1
00:00:00,668 --> 00:00:02,736
[*****]

2
00:00:02,870 --> 00:00:05,306
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

3
00:00:14,915 --> 00:00:16,617
[KIDS LAUGHING]

4
00:00:19,220 --> 00:00:20,554
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

5
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:34,802
[CLATTERING]

6
00:01:25,286 --> 00:01:26,487
GEORGIA: The supplies
for the shelter

7
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,289
will be picked up next Saturday

8
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:30,658
between the hours
of 9:00 and 12:00.

9
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:32,326
Make sure someone's home.

10
00:01:32,893 --> 00:01:34,762
And Ellie,
I know from experience

11
00:01:34,895 --> 00:01:36,897
that sometimes
you don't hear the doorbell

12
00:01:37,030 --> 00:01:38,432
when you're working
in your garden.

13
00:01:38,566 --> 00:01:40,534
Well, my garden is my sanctuary.

14
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:41,902
Fiddlesticks.

15
00:01:42,035 --> 00:01:43,504
You stay in next Saturday
and needlepoint.

16
00:01:43,637 --> 00:01:44,738
Well, yes, ma'am.

17
00:01:45,005 --> 00:01:48,742
Last order of business,
the Peach Gala Dinner.

18
00:01:49,042 --> 00:01:51,879
The RSVPs are pouring in,
and I think we are going to have

19
00:01:52,012 --> 00:01:53,647
a bigger turn-out
than last year.

20
00:01:53,781 --> 00:01:55,316
ELLEN: Last year
we didn't have the governor

21
00:01:55,616 --> 00:01:57,084
of Georgia in attendance.

22
00:01:57,285 --> 00:01:59,253
Oh, last year
we didn't have a lot of things

23
00:01:59,387 --> 00:02:00,888
we're going to have this year,

24
00:02:01,255 --> 00:02:03,191
thanks
to my gracious sister-in-law,

25
00:02:03,257 --> 00:02:04,258
Miss Madeleine Porter,

26
00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:07,595
and her generous donation
of her lovely home

27
00:02:07,728 --> 00:02:09,297
for the evening.

28
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:12,333
Well, it's the least I could do
for such a worthy cause.

29
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:17,305
Ellen, put that foul thing out.
You told Jack you'd quit.

30
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:20,408
-I did quit. Just now.
-[GEORGIA CHUCKLING]

31
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:22,410
Georgia, please tell me

32
00:02:22,543 --> 00:02:24,478
you are considering
taking a date to the gala.

33
00:02:24,612 --> 00:02:27,515
I am going to be working
that room for donations.

34
00:02:27,648 --> 00:02:29,850
I just won't have any time
for entertaining a date.

35
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,985
My God, Georgia,
it's been a year.

36
00:02:32,119 --> 00:02:33,787
It's time you get back
in the game.

37
00:02:34,355 --> 00:02:35,923
MADELEINE:
Loosen your belts, girls.

38
00:02:36,123 --> 00:02:37,825
Here comes Georgia's apple pie.

39
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:39,227
Betty, be careful
with that dish.

40
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,729
It belonged
to Georgia's great-grandmother.

41
00:02:41,862 --> 00:02:42,863
Yes, ma'am.

42
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,832
She maintains that a pie
in that dish

43
00:02:44,965 --> 00:02:47,901
was made superior
by its age and experience.

44
00:02:48,302 --> 00:02:50,371
-There goes my diet.
-What diet?

45
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:51,972
The one I fully intend to start

46
00:02:52,105 --> 00:02:53,774
as soon as you quit
your smoking.

47
00:02:53,907 --> 00:02:55,075
[CHUCKLES]

48
00:03:03,417 --> 00:03:05,253
ANSWERING MACHINE:
You have one message.

49
00:03:05,353 --> 00:03:09,022
Message one.
Wednesday, 11:13 a.m.

50
00:03:09,156 --> 00:03:12,293
JANE: Mrs. Porter,
this is Jane Cramer.

51
00:03:12,826 --> 00:03:16,264
I'm a patient representative
at San Diego General Hospital.

52
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:18,699
I found your number
in your daughter's purse.

53
00:03:18,832 --> 00:03:20,401
She's been in an accident.

54
00:03:21,134 --> 00:03:23,637
Please call me as soon
as you get this message.

55
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:26,407
JANE: It's a matter
of some urgency.

56
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:29,810
I can be reached
at extension 216.

57
00:03:29,943 --> 00:03:31,379
[*****]

58
00:03:33,013 --> 00:03:35,383
WOMAN ON PA: ...to Atlanta
and connecting to...

59
00:03:35,949 --> 00:03:37,385
GEORGIA: I love you, Lily-Joe.

60
00:03:38,286 --> 00:03:40,454
LILY-JOE: I love you
to the stars and back.

61
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:42,423
GEORGIA: I love you
to the stars and back

62
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:44,858
-and around the moon. [LAUGHING]
-[LILY-JOE LAUGHING]

63
00:03:45,326 --> 00:03:47,861
Well, I love you
to the stars, back,

64
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:49,497
and around the moon

65
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,732
and to the last corner
of the universe.

66
00:03:51,865 --> 00:03:53,934
GEORGIA: Me too, babe.
[CHUCKLING]

67
00:03:56,837 --> 00:03:59,407
Night, mama.
Roses on your pillow.

68
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:01,309
GEORGIA: Roses on your pillow.

69
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:05,746
Ma'am, you're boarding.

70
00:04:06,146 --> 00:04:07,781
-All right.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER ON PA]

71
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,789
WOMAN: Ma'am,
you're boarding pass, please?

72
00:04:20,127 --> 00:04:22,062
[SIREN WAILING]

73
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:26,834
JANE: Mrs. Porter?

74
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:30,170
-I'm Jane Cramer. I called you.
-GEORGIA: How is she?

75
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:33,206
Dr. Peterson would like
to talk to you.

76
00:04:34,408 --> 00:04:35,976
Well, I'd like to see
my daughter first.

77
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:37,378
He should be here any minute.

78
00:04:38,846 --> 00:04:41,515
It just took forever
getting here,

79
00:04:41,715 --> 00:04:44,452
but I was very lucky to--
to be able to get
a plane right away.

80
00:04:44,585 --> 00:04:47,621
Mrs. Porter, it would really
be better if you waited.

81
00:04:49,357 --> 00:04:50,358
Why?

82
00:04:51,359 --> 00:04:52,660
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

83
00:05:00,468 --> 00:05:01,569
[GEORGIA GASPING]

84
00:05:02,836 --> 00:05:05,138
How bad is she?
The nurse wouldn't tell me.

85
00:05:08,275 --> 00:05:09,276
I'm sorry.

86
00:05:09,643 --> 00:05:11,912
-Oh.
-Massive internal injuries.

87
00:05:12,112 --> 00:05:13,847
GEORGIA: Oh, no.

88
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,117
[CRYING]

89
00:05:20,488 --> 00:05:21,522
No.

90
00:05:23,391 --> 00:05:25,025
No, I don't believe it.

91
00:05:25,626 --> 00:05:28,396
-That's a lie. No, no.
-[DR. PETERSON SHUSHING]

92
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:31,399
-DR. PETERSON: It's okay.
-Oh, oh, God!

93
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:35,002
GEORGIA: No, no, please...

94
00:05:37,237 --> 00:05:40,408
No, not my baby. [SOBBING]

95
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:44,177
DR. PETERSON: We thought
it would be best

96
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:46,647
-if you told the child.
-[SOBS]

97
00:05:56,624 --> 00:05:57,758
The child?

98
00:05:58,158 --> 00:05:59,860
DR. PETERSON: Don't worry,
she's fine.

99
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,996
The fact that she was belted in
probably saved her.

100
00:06:03,731 --> 00:06:05,433
Except for a few cuts
and bruises

101
00:06:05,499 --> 00:06:07,134
we expect her to fully recover.

102
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,870
What do you say? Uh...

103
00:06:13,807 --> 00:06:15,443
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

104
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:18,912
DR. PETERSON:
She's just down here.

105
00:06:21,482 --> 00:06:23,116
NURSE: Doctor,
can you take a look at this?

106
00:06:25,185 --> 00:06:26,186
I'll be right in.

107
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:35,896
Hi.

108
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:40,067
That's a nice elephant
you got there.

109
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:42,636
Mrs. Porter...

110
00:06:44,137 --> 00:06:45,305
we're over here.

111
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:47,140
Excuse me.

112
00:06:50,177 --> 00:06:51,311
DR. PETERSON: Jacey.

113
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,081
I brought you a visitor.

114
00:06:59,887 --> 00:07:01,354
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

115
00:07:07,861 --> 00:07:10,664
Don't worry about her arm.
She has a few stitches,

116
00:07:10,798 --> 00:07:12,299
but I don't expect
they'll leave a scar.

117
00:07:16,604 --> 00:07:17,905
I'll leave you two to talk.

118
00:07:23,911 --> 00:07:24,912
Doctor?

119
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:32,385
I don't understand.

120
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,054
DR. PETERSON: What?

121
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:36,256
Who is this child?

122
00:07:37,224 --> 00:07:38,592
I-- isn't she
your granddaughter?

123
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:42,663
Well, I haven't talked
to my daughter

124
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:44,131
in over nine years.

125
00:07:44,832 --> 00:07:45,899
We had a falling out.

126
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:49,537
She's a black child.

127
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:54,241
DR. PETERSON: Well, her--
her father was African-American.

128
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:56,409
Your daughter's husband.

129
00:07:57,410 --> 00:07:58,746
He died at the scene.

130
00:07:58,879 --> 00:08:00,380
I'm sorry.
I thought you knew that.

131
00:08:00,581 --> 00:08:01,582
[PAGER BEEPING]

132
00:08:04,618 --> 00:08:06,119
We pulled the child's records.

133
00:08:06,419 --> 00:08:08,355
You were the only relative
we were able to contact.

134
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:11,458
You can take her home tomorrow.

135
00:08:12,860 --> 00:08:13,861
Take her?

136
00:08:14,394 --> 00:08:15,629
DR. PETERSON: Well, yes.

137
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:18,098
If you don't,
she'll be put in foster care.

138
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:22,402
She needs to be close
to someone right now.

139
00:08:23,571 --> 00:08:25,238
She doesn't remember anything
about the accident.

140
00:08:25,372 --> 00:08:27,641
But at some point she will,
and she'll need to have--

141
00:08:27,775 --> 00:08:30,110
-[BEEPER BEEPING]
-I'm sorry.

142
00:08:30,878 --> 00:08:33,781
I have to go.
I'll be back as soon as I can.

143
00:08:47,094 --> 00:08:48,261
Hi.

144
00:08:49,396 --> 00:08:50,798
I'm thirsty.

145
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:04,077
GEORGIA: Here you are.

146
00:09:09,617 --> 00:09:10,618
Thank you.

147
00:09:11,084 --> 00:09:12,085
You're welcome.

148
00:09:14,622 --> 00:09:15,656
[*****]

149
00:09:16,724 --> 00:09:18,025
Your name is Jacey.

150
00:09:20,027 --> 00:09:21,028
It's a pretty name.

151
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:23,631
Very southern.

152
00:09:25,332 --> 00:09:28,636
Howard Binkman
calls me J.C. Penny.

153
00:09:29,102 --> 00:09:32,940
A boy teases you
it means he likes you.

154
00:09:35,108 --> 00:09:36,176
Your mother...

155
00:09:38,278 --> 00:09:39,346
what's her name?

156
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,715
Lily-Joe.

157
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:43,951
[*****]

158
00:09:47,721 --> 00:09:48,789
And your father?

159
00:09:49,657 --> 00:09:51,792
Marcus P. Hastings.

160
00:09:53,761 --> 00:09:55,095
Oh, my God.

161
00:09:56,296 --> 00:09:59,399
What time is it when an elephant
sits on a fence?

162
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:04,805
Time to get a new fence.

163
00:10:07,808 --> 00:10:09,643
I was a nurse once
for Halloween

164
00:10:09,777 --> 00:10:10,944
when I was little.

165
00:10:12,212 --> 00:10:13,881
Oh, I'm not a nurse, honey.

166
00:10:14,782 --> 00:10:16,083
Then what are you?

167
00:10:19,887 --> 00:10:22,389
Your mother, Lily-Joe...

168
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:26,393
Your mother is my daughter.

169
00:10:27,094 --> 00:10:30,497
Uh-huh. That's not true.
I would know you already.

170
00:10:31,231 --> 00:10:32,700
You would be my grandma.

171
00:10:33,834 --> 00:10:35,202
Well, I live in Georgia.

172
00:10:36,069 --> 00:10:37,805
That's pretty far from here.

173
00:10:40,774 --> 00:10:42,342
Did your mother
ever say anything

174
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,077
about growing up in Georgia?

175
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:46,714
A farm?

176
00:10:47,881 --> 00:10:50,450
-School?
-I want my mom.

177
00:10:51,451 --> 00:10:52,753
-Can you get my mom?
-GEORGIA: Honey.

178
00:10:54,221 --> 00:10:55,555
Your mama...

179
00:10:57,157 --> 00:10:58,959
and your daddy, uh...

180
00:11:00,293 --> 00:11:01,729
There was a...

181
00:11:02,863 --> 00:11:04,732
There was a terrible accident.

182
00:11:05,966 --> 00:11:07,300
No.

183
00:11:07,735 --> 00:11:09,436
-No.
-Uh, honey,
it's going to be okay.

184
00:11:09,569 --> 00:11:12,439
-Mommy. Daddy.
-It's going to be okay.

185
00:11:12,572 --> 00:11:15,008
-JACEY: Go away. Mommy.
-Honey...

186
00:11:15,142 --> 00:11:17,344
-Daddy. Come back, Mommy.
-Honey...

187
00:11:17,644 --> 00:11:19,913
-Honey... Please, Mommy, Daddy.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

188
00:11:20,047 --> 00:11:22,816
-I'm so sorry.
-JACEY: Please come back.

189
00:11:23,383 --> 00:11:24,952
[JACEY CRYING]

190
00:11:25,986 --> 00:11:27,087
I'm sorry.

191
00:11:30,758 --> 00:11:31,925
[*****]

192
00:11:47,574 --> 00:11:48,976
[CAR APPROACHING]

193
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,015
JOE: You stay right here.
Let-- go of me.

194
00:11:55,148 --> 00:11:56,249
GEORGIA: Joe.

195
00:11:58,786 --> 00:12:00,888
No, no, come on home, Joe.
Come on.

196
00:12:01,021 --> 00:12:02,189
-JOE: Stay in the car, Georgia.
-Come on.

197
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:04,091
JOE: Get back.
Just stay put, Georgia.

198
00:12:04,457 --> 00:12:05,793
[DOG BARKING]

199
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:07,895
-GEORGIA: Joe.
-[GUN COCKS]

200
00:12:08,028 --> 00:12:10,663
[GUNSHOTS]

201
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,868
[*****]

202
00:12:16,269 --> 00:12:17,404
JACEY: Mama.

203
00:12:30,283 --> 00:12:31,852
WOMAN ON PA: May I have
your attention, please?

204
00:12:32,152 --> 00:12:35,956
This is the final boarding call
for flight 710 to Atlanta.

205
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:37,324
-Passengers...
-GEORGIA: Honey,

206
00:12:38,325 --> 00:12:40,027
won't you take a little sip
of this?

207
00:12:41,394 --> 00:12:43,363
You haven't had anything
all day.

208
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,267
How about a little chocolate?

209
00:12:48,135 --> 00:12:49,970
I never hear a child
who didn't like chocolate.

210
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:51,538
I'm allergic to chocolate.

211
00:12:52,239 --> 00:12:53,473
I'll throw up.

212
00:12:54,842 --> 00:12:57,144
Really? I'm sorry.

213
00:12:57,277 --> 00:12:58,611
WOMAN ON PA: Can I have
your attention, please?

214
00:12:58,745 --> 00:13:01,448
-This the final warning call...
-That's not heaven.

215
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:04,651
GEORGIA: Oh, no, you're right.
That isn't heaven.

216
00:13:05,218 --> 00:13:06,653
Heaven is hidden from us.

217
00:13:06,854 --> 00:13:11,992
It's-- in the last corner
of the universe.

218
00:13:12,893 --> 00:13:13,894
Why?

219
00:13:15,428 --> 00:13:19,666
Well, um,
maybe it's just so beautiful

220
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:24,872
that we'd want to go live there
before our time.

221
00:13:25,405 --> 00:13:29,509
[*****]

222
00:13:33,713 --> 00:13:35,048
[KIDS LAUGHING]

223
00:13:38,886 --> 00:13:41,454
GEORGIA: This is it.
This is Sweet Creek.

224
00:13:41,588 --> 00:13:43,256
This is where your mother
grew up.

225
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:46,193
You've come at a good time
when the hydrangeas

226
00:13:46,326 --> 00:13:47,560
are still blooming.

227
00:13:57,437 --> 00:13:59,072
-DRIVER: Here you go, ma'am.
-GEORGIA: Thank you.

228
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:02,209
All right, here we are.

229
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,979
I'mma arrange to have
all your things sent here.

230
00:14:06,313 --> 00:14:08,081
JACEY: Why is it so hot?

231
00:14:08,781 --> 00:14:10,417
GEORGIA: Well, honey,
this is the south.

232
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:12,052
We just have more sun here.

233
00:14:13,553 --> 00:14:15,422
Pretty soon it'll seem
just like home.

234
00:14:17,524 --> 00:14:18,926
[KIDS TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

235
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:25,999
-ALL: Surprise.
-[GEORGIA CHUCKLING]

236
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:28,301
-Welcome home.
-GEORGIA: My word.

237
00:14:28,635 --> 00:14:30,403
MADELEINE: Now where
is that grand-niece of mine?

238
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:33,941
[CHUCKLES]

239
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:38,946
-GEORGIA: Jacey.
-[LAUGHS]

240
00:14:42,349 --> 00:14:43,350
Oh.

241
00:14:43,984 --> 00:14:45,185
GEORGIA: I told my friends
about you

242
00:14:45,318 --> 00:14:48,488
so they planned
a little welcome home surprise.

243
00:14:50,357 --> 00:14:51,858
These are my friends.

244
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:55,395
These are the Georgia Peaches.

245
00:14:56,529 --> 00:14:59,732
[CHUCKLES] Welcome
to Sweet Creek, honey.

246
00:15:00,968 --> 00:15:02,235
JACEY: Thank you.

247
00:15:04,537 --> 00:15:05,638
MADELEINE: Hello, Jacey.

248
00:15:06,073 --> 00:15:07,340
It's nice to meet you.

249
00:15:07,774 --> 00:15:10,610
You know you look
just like your mother except...

250
00:15:12,379 --> 00:15:15,382
Except your eyes are brown
and your mother's were blue.

251
00:15:15,782 --> 00:15:18,851
Why, you have
your grandma's eyes.

252
00:15:20,053 --> 00:15:21,388
-[ELLEN CHUCKLING]
-GEORGIA: Come on, honey,

253
00:15:21,521 --> 00:15:24,691
I'll show you to your room
right up the stairs from me.

254
00:15:31,564 --> 00:15:33,866
GEORGIA: You know, this room
used to be your mama's room.

255
00:15:35,168 --> 00:15:37,137
She helped me make
this very quilt.

256
00:15:40,007 --> 00:15:43,610
Uh, oh, look at this.
Wow!

257
00:15:44,144 --> 00:15:46,713
Well, I think the Peaches
must have just--

258
00:15:47,214 --> 00:15:49,716
Just bought out every store,
just for you.

259
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:51,751
Is your arm hurting you, honey?

260
00:15:52,452 --> 00:15:53,553
Is...

261
00:15:55,255 --> 00:15:56,856
Well, don't-- don't you worry.

262
00:15:57,657 --> 00:15:59,226
We'll go down Monday
and have the doctor

263
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:01,228
take a look
at those old stitches.

264
00:16:03,763 --> 00:16:05,232
You must be worn out.

265
00:16:09,036 --> 00:16:10,870
You know... [EXHALES DEEPLY]

266
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:13,173
...I never was able to--

267
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:16,043
to put your mama's clothes
away.

268
00:16:18,911 --> 00:16:20,380
But it's time now.

269
00:16:21,414 --> 00:16:22,882
I'm going to clean out
this closet,

270
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,517
and it's going to be
just for you.

271
00:16:26,386 --> 00:16:27,854
Oh, my God.

272
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:31,491
Georgia,
why didn't you tell us?

273
00:16:31,624 --> 00:16:32,625
[SIGHS] I...

274
00:16:33,593 --> 00:16:35,428
I just didn't know what to say.

275
00:16:36,296 --> 00:16:38,698
I still can't believe
this whole thing has happened.

276
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,369
They were going to put her
in foster care.

277
00:16:43,136 --> 00:16:44,637
Are you sure she's Lily's?

278
00:16:45,072 --> 00:16:48,641
Well, of course she's Lily's.
She's the spitting image of her.

279
00:16:49,876 --> 00:16:51,844
Well, there must be someone
who can take her.

280
00:16:52,079 --> 00:16:55,415
Take her where?
She's Georgia's grandchild.

281
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:57,784
A child is always a blessing.

282
00:16:59,086 --> 00:17:00,187
[*****]

283
00:17:01,921 --> 00:17:03,223
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

284
00:17:05,692 --> 00:17:06,693
GEORGIA: Honey?

285
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:09,562
Honey, are you in here?

286
00:17:21,108 --> 00:17:22,942
Oh, come on, sweetheart.

287
00:17:25,245 --> 00:17:26,513
[GRUNTING]

288
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,382
Come on. Let's go to beddy.

289
00:17:31,718 --> 00:17:33,886
There, there.

290
00:17:34,954 --> 00:17:36,723
Upsie-daisy.

291
00:17:37,357 --> 00:17:38,391
Here.

292
00:17:49,602 --> 00:17:51,138
Roses on your pillow.

293
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:05,152
[*****]

294
00:18:28,675 --> 00:18:30,610
JOE: I'm only giving you
one more minute

295
00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:32,812
and then I am coming in there
after you.

296
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,181
[GUN COCKING]

297
00:18:36,516 --> 00:18:37,684
LOU: Joe, what the hell
you doing?

298
00:18:39,852 --> 00:18:41,721
JOE: I'm going to give
that boy of yours what for.

299
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:43,290
LOU: Marcus, get back
in the house.

300
00:18:43,423 --> 00:18:44,691
-MARCUS: Dad.
-LOU: Get back in the house.

301
00:18:45,925 --> 00:18:47,026
Take that gun off my boy, Joe.

302
00:18:48,295 --> 00:18:51,631
Look at you... [LAUGHS]
...drunk as a skunk.

303
00:18:52,699 --> 00:18:54,767
-Put the gun down.
-Just get out of my face, Lou.

304
00:18:54,901 --> 00:18:57,237
-Get out--- get out
of the way, Lou.
-LOU: Put the gun down.

305
00:18:57,370 --> 00:18:58,971
-JOE: You-- Maybe you need
a whooping too.
-GEORGIA: Joe...

306
00:18:59,105 --> 00:19:00,240
[GROANS]

307
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:02,074
-GEORGIA: Oh!
-MARCUS: Stop it.

308
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,411
LILY-JOE: What do you want, Dad?

309
00:19:06,679 --> 00:19:07,780
You want me, Dad?

310
00:19:08,648 --> 00:19:10,283
-Fine.
-Joe, this is crazy. Come on.

311
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:12,084
Fine. You kill us both.

312
00:19:12,219 --> 00:19:13,486
-She is coming home
with us tonight.
-No, you're not--

313
00:19:13,620 --> 00:19:15,288
-I promise you that.
-[GEORGIA GROANS]

314
00:19:15,422 --> 00:19:17,924
-MARCUS: Mrs. Porter.
-I won't ever come home
while you're still alive.

315
00:19:18,124 --> 00:19:19,459
-[GUN COCKS]
-GEORGIA: No.

316
00:19:19,826 --> 00:19:22,128
No. Go, go in the house.

317
00:19:22,429 --> 00:19:24,431
JOE: Georgia, get
in the car now.

318
00:19:24,564 --> 00:19:25,998
Mama, don't go with him.

319
00:19:26,132 --> 00:19:27,667
-Don't go with him.
-JOE: Georgia, get
in this car now.

320
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:30,136
-MARCUS: Stay here.
Stay here with us.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

321
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,305
-JOE: In this car.
-[GEORGIA GRUNTING]

322
00:19:32,439 --> 00:19:34,341
You just better pray
she comes home.

323
00:19:34,474 --> 00:19:37,109
-[GEORGIA GROANING]
-LILY-JOE: Mother, mother.

324
00:19:37,244 --> 00:19:38,778
GEORGIA: No, I'm all right.
I'm all right.

325
00:19:39,145 --> 00:19:41,848
-Mother.
-[CAR DOOR CLOSING]

326
00:19:46,719 --> 00:19:48,955
LILY-JOE: Mom. Mother.

327
00:19:49,155 --> 00:19:51,558
JACEY: Mommy. [CRYING]

328
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,628
Mommy.

329
00:19:57,464 --> 00:19:59,499
Mommy. Daddy.

330
00:20:00,267 --> 00:20:01,468
Mommy.

331
00:20:02,335 --> 00:20:04,437
Daddy. [CRYING]

332
00:20:04,571 --> 00:20:07,607
-Honey, honey, no.
-[CRIES]

333
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:09,309
Oh, it's all right.
It's all right.

334
00:20:09,442 --> 00:20:11,944
I'm here. I'm here.

335
00:20:13,713 --> 00:20:16,849
* My baby buys me... *

336
00:20:18,184 --> 00:20:21,888
* Daddy's gonna love it *

337
00:20:28,861 --> 00:20:30,363
No, she's still sleeping.

338
00:20:30,497 --> 00:20:32,499
She must be exhausted,
poor thing.

339
00:20:33,866 --> 00:20:36,168
I'm making all
of her mother's favorite dishes.

340
00:20:36,369 --> 00:20:39,306
-[DOORBELL RINGING]
-Shoot, there's the doorbell.

341
00:20:39,639 --> 00:20:41,408
It must be the man
from the shelter.

342
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:43,376
Madeleine, I'll call you
right back.

343
00:20:48,114 --> 00:20:49,248
Good morning.

344
00:20:49,382 --> 00:20:51,618
Uh, the box is right at the side
of the house.

345
00:20:51,884 --> 00:20:53,119
You want to be real careful
with it

346
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,454
because there are some
good dishes.

347
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:55,888
You know, don't let them slide.

348
00:20:58,725 --> 00:20:59,759
Is there a problem?

349
00:21:01,027 --> 00:21:03,396
Where's your truck?
JACEY: Grandpa.

350
00:21:04,196 --> 00:21:05,231
GEORGIA: Oh.

351
00:21:14,341 --> 00:21:15,942
It's okay, little bear,
I'm here now.

352
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:17,910
Everything's going
to be just fine.

353
00:21:20,613 --> 00:21:24,216
-Mommy and Daddy are gone.
-I know. I know.

354
00:21:24,717 --> 00:21:26,052
[*****]

355
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:29,989
[JACEY SOBBING]

356
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:32,825
LOU: I was away

357
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:34,794
or I would have been here
much sooner.

358
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,436
-You don't remember me, do you?
-GEORGIA: No.

359
00:21:43,836 --> 00:21:46,373
I mean, yes, of course.
You're Marcus's father.

360
00:21:46,639 --> 00:21:47,774
I'm-- I'm sorry.

361
00:21:47,907 --> 00:21:49,376
I thought you were
from the homeless shelter.

362
00:21:50,009 --> 00:21:51,378
Of course you did.

363
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:57,984
Are you ready?

364
00:21:58,385 --> 00:21:59,819
-JACEY: Mm-hmm.
-Okay.

365
00:22:01,988 --> 00:22:03,022
Ready for what?

366
00:22:04,090 --> 00:22:05,157
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

367
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:08,194
I'm taking Jacey home...

368
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:11,631
where she belongs.

369
00:22:12,131 --> 00:22:15,067
[*****]

370
00:22:22,775 --> 00:22:24,777
GEORGIA: Well, you do realize
she just got here.

371
00:22:25,512 --> 00:22:28,214
We haven't had a chance to get
to know each other at all.

372
00:22:28,415 --> 00:22:30,650
Grandpa, I want to go home.

373
00:22:31,784 --> 00:22:32,785
I know you do.

374
00:22:33,285 --> 00:22:35,788
Hey, if you go over there
on the porch

375
00:22:36,789 --> 00:22:38,925
there's a pre-birthday present
there for you.

376
00:22:39,426 --> 00:22:41,761
-It's right over there.
-Okay.

377
00:22:45,532 --> 00:22:46,766
[LOU EXHALING DEEPLY]

378
00:22:48,034 --> 00:22:49,636
Oh. Yes, please.

379
00:22:58,310 --> 00:23:00,312
I bet you didn't know
she existed, did you?

380
00:23:02,248 --> 00:23:03,450
-No.
-LOU: Yeah.

381
00:23:04,083 --> 00:23:05,885
Lily and Marcus didn't want you
or your husband

382
00:23:06,018 --> 00:23:07,520
to have anything to do
with that child.

383
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,922
My husband died over a year ago.

384
00:23:10,056 --> 00:23:12,925
Oh, sorry, for the loss.

385
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:17,029
He's perfect, Grandpa.
I love him so much.

386
00:23:17,497 --> 00:23:18,965
-So, what's his name?
-[MEOWS]

387
00:23:19,098 --> 00:23:22,234
-Mm, Smoky.
-Smoky? Another Smoky?

388
00:23:22,669 --> 00:23:25,505
-Smoky Number Two.
-Hey, Smoky Number Two.

389
00:23:25,972 --> 00:23:28,475
Well, she's just cute as a bug.
You like cats?

390
00:23:28,608 --> 00:23:30,477
Uh, Jacey was a cat
in her last life.

391
00:23:30,943 --> 00:23:31,944
I see.

392
00:23:32,378 --> 00:23:34,481
-I guess I have a lot to learn.
-LOU: Yeah

393
00:23:36,583 --> 00:23:38,184
What happened
to Smoky Number One?

394
00:23:38,485 --> 00:23:41,053
-Grandpa, I'm hungry.
-GEORGIA: I-- I cooked.

395
00:23:41,521 --> 00:23:43,956
I, uh, I cooked chicken and rice

396
00:23:44,090 --> 00:23:46,493
-and some--
-I want your food, Grandpa.

397
00:23:46,593 --> 00:23:47,727
LOU: Okay.

398
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:50,162
No, you take Smoky Number Two
out and play,

399
00:23:50,597 --> 00:23:53,800
and I'll make you something
very, very special.

400
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,101
-Okay.
-All right.

401
00:23:55,802 --> 00:23:56,903
[CAT MEOWING]

402
00:23:58,938 --> 00:23:59,939
May I?

403
00:24:01,508 --> 00:24:02,609
Of course.

404
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,118
-This is it.
-[SIZZLING]

405
00:24:20,593 --> 00:24:21,861
Ah.

406
00:24:25,397 --> 00:24:26,398
Milk?

407
00:24:34,807 --> 00:24:35,975
-Here you are.
-Hmm.

408
00:24:42,048 --> 00:24:43,650
[SIGHS] Just
because I'm curious,

409
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:46,085
how did you ever expect
to raise a black child

410
00:24:46,218 --> 00:24:47,353
here in Sweet Creek?

411
00:24:48,220 --> 00:24:49,722
-Well, she's only half black.
-Well...

412
00:24:51,558 --> 00:24:53,459
and this is the south.
One drop of black blood

413
00:24:53,593 --> 00:24:54,861
makes you black for life.

414
00:24:55,928 --> 00:24:57,396
You ought to know that better
than I do.

415
00:24:57,964 --> 00:24:59,966
-You know things are changing.
-[GRUNTS]

416
00:25:00,099 --> 00:25:01,834
This town is as progressive as--

417
00:25:01,968 --> 00:25:03,069
When was the last time

418
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:04,904
you had a black man here
in your kitchen?

419
00:25:05,471 --> 00:25:06,873
I hardly think that's pertinent.

420
00:25:07,006 --> 00:25:09,308
I mean, you've probably
never had a black man

421
00:25:09,441 --> 00:25:10,577
in your house at all,

422
00:25:10,643 --> 00:25:12,011
unless he was
in here fixing something.

423
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:16,248
Why don't you pack up
her things.

424
00:25:16,382 --> 00:25:17,817
I'll take her away
this afternoon.

425
00:25:20,587 --> 00:25:21,821
I am sorry, but...

426
00:25:23,856 --> 00:25:26,659
you can't take her.
I won't allow it.

427
00:25:30,329 --> 00:25:31,497
You don't have a choice.

428
00:25:31,631 --> 00:25:33,600
I have been appointed
her legal guardian

429
00:25:34,166 --> 00:25:35,301
in their will.

430
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,905
Lily and Marcus left Jacey
to me.

431
00:25:40,472 --> 00:25:42,775
Jacey will never be raised here
in Sweet Creek.

432
00:25:43,610 --> 00:25:45,878
Jacey, the rice pudding
is almost ready.

433
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:53,319
-[CAT MEOWS]
-Mm.

434
00:25:54,253 --> 00:25:55,354
[LAUGHS]

435
00:25:58,124 --> 00:26:00,760
I would like to take her
to the doctor Monday morning.

436
00:26:01,628 --> 00:26:04,463
I told her I would be with her
when the stitches came out.

437
00:26:05,765 --> 00:26:08,267
I want to do this one thing
with her.

438
00:26:09,836 --> 00:26:10,837
If I may.

439
00:26:16,042 --> 00:26:18,277
All right. I got some business
to attend to here

440
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,846
in Sweet Creek.

441
00:26:20,346 --> 00:26:23,549
We'll leave Monday afternoon
for San Diego.

442
00:26:23,950 --> 00:26:25,084
Thank you for that.

443
00:26:25,785 --> 00:26:27,654
I'll be at that motel
on Cherry Street.

444
00:26:30,256 --> 00:26:31,190
Little bear,

445
00:26:32,058 --> 00:26:33,793
-I will see you tomorrow.
-JACEY: No.

446
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:35,494
-GEORGIA: I'll make supper.
-That'll be fine.

447
00:26:36,262 --> 00:26:38,230
-Give me a hug. Give me a hug.
-No.

448
00:26:38,665 --> 00:26:40,332
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
-JACEY: No.

449
00:26:43,169 --> 00:26:44,436
LOU: Okay. Go ahead.

450
00:26:47,674 --> 00:26:50,209
Jacey, come on.
Let's us girls go shopping.

451
00:26:52,679 --> 00:26:53,946
Bye, Grandpa.

452
00:26:55,381 --> 00:26:56,949
-Come on, honey.
-[CAT MEOWING]

453
00:26:57,750 --> 00:27:01,053
I know a place we can get
a beautiful new dress

454
00:27:01,187 --> 00:27:02,755
for church tomorrow.

455
00:27:06,693 --> 00:27:08,928
Why do I have to take a bath
in the day?

456
00:27:09,228 --> 00:27:12,098
GEORGIA: Because it's Sunday,
and because you're a girl,

457
00:27:12,231 --> 00:27:15,034
and girls should smell sweet
at church.

458
00:27:15,702 --> 00:27:17,603
Oh, I love this shampoo.

459
00:27:17,937 --> 00:27:20,840
It smells just like coconuts
from Hawaii.

460
00:27:22,108 --> 00:27:24,076
I got it out
of a Hawaiian catalog

461
00:27:24,210 --> 00:27:25,778
called Aloha Shopper.

462
00:27:27,346 --> 00:27:28,447
[GRUNTING]

463
00:27:30,983 --> 00:27:33,085
See. [GRUNTING]

464
00:27:34,453 --> 00:27:36,588
[GROANS] Coconut hurts my eyes.

465
00:27:36,723 --> 00:27:38,891
-That's not how Mommy does it.
-Oh, here. I'm sorry.

466
00:27:39,591 --> 00:27:40,727
Just a little more water.

467
00:27:40,793 --> 00:27:42,528
-I want mommy
-I know.

468
00:27:45,364 --> 00:27:46,498
So do I.

469
00:27:50,602 --> 00:27:51,738
[CHURCH BELL TOLLING]

470
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:54,774
[*****]

471
00:27:55,574 --> 00:27:57,443
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

472
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:15,561
-Gotcha.
-[GROANS]

473
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,769
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

474
00:28:27,073 --> 00:28:29,275
All right, honey, um,
bow your head.

475
00:28:31,243 --> 00:28:33,980
Dear Lord, we thank you
for your blessings.

476
00:28:34,881 --> 00:28:36,916
Help us to be worthy
of your love.

477
00:28:38,084 --> 00:28:41,153
We pray for Lily-Joe
and Marcus,

478
00:28:41,387 --> 00:28:44,023
and we know they're with you.

479
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:45,657
They're part of your flock,

480
00:28:45,792 --> 00:28:47,927
but they will be in our hearts
forever.

481
00:28:48,928 --> 00:28:51,397
And thank you
for sending me Jacey.

482
00:28:52,464 --> 00:28:54,133
-Amen.
-Amen.

483
00:28:56,668 --> 00:29:00,006
[*****]

484
00:29:01,407 --> 00:29:03,843
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

485
00:29:38,845 --> 00:29:45,484
[*****]

486
00:30:06,338 --> 00:30:08,140
LOU: Put your head there,
right up against this post now.

487
00:30:09,375 --> 00:30:11,043
Well, let's see
what we got here.

488
00:30:12,511 --> 00:30:14,046
I think this is going
to be a world record.

489
00:30:15,247 --> 00:30:17,016
My goodness, look at that.

490
00:30:17,149 --> 00:30:19,051
You have gained
three and a half inches

491
00:30:19,185 --> 00:30:20,186
since the last time
we measured.

492
00:30:20,519 --> 00:30:22,521
Boy, what have you been eating?

493
00:30:23,089 --> 00:30:24,090
Huh?

494
00:30:25,024 --> 00:30:26,025
[CAR DOOR CLOSING]

495
00:30:40,539 --> 00:30:42,408
-Morning.
-Morning.

496
00:30:46,512 --> 00:30:48,814
-Stop, you're hurting me.
-GEORGIA: Well, I'm sorry.

497
00:30:48,948 --> 00:30:52,418
I just can't get through
this comb to work. Never mind.

498
00:30:53,085 --> 00:30:55,221
-Hi, Betty.
-BETTY: Hello, Mrs. Porter.

499
00:30:55,354 --> 00:30:56,788
And who's this sweet thing?

500
00:30:56,923 --> 00:30:58,757
This is Jacey. My...

501
00:31:00,626 --> 00:31:03,996
-Jacey, you want to shake hands.
-BETTY: Well, hello, Jacey.

502
00:31:04,696 --> 00:31:05,998
Aren't you a pretty girl?

503
00:31:06,765 --> 00:31:08,000
And how old are you?

504
00:31:08,467 --> 00:31:10,937
-Six and three quarters.
-BETTY: Really?

505
00:31:11,237 --> 00:31:13,973
Betty, I need to talk to
Mr. and Mrs. Porter for a bit.

506
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:15,841
Could you just keep an eye
on her for me?

507
00:31:15,975 --> 00:31:17,977
Oh, yes, ma'am.
I could use the company.

508
00:31:19,946 --> 00:31:21,147
Come on with me.

509
00:31:22,481 --> 00:31:24,951
I was just thinking of having
an ice cold lemonade.

510
00:31:25,084 --> 00:31:27,686
-Would you like some?
-Yes, please.

511
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:31,057
Larry, thanks so much
for talking to me on Sunday.

512
00:31:31,457 --> 00:31:32,959
I know this is your golf day.

513
00:31:33,592 --> 00:31:35,962
Georgia, please, you're family.

514
00:31:36,828 --> 00:31:39,631
Now this here document
gives him full legal custody.

515
00:31:40,299 --> 00:31:42,101
This kind of thing
is hard to fight.

516
00:31:42,534 --> 00:31:44,770
But I am her grandmother.

517
00:31:45,004 --> 00:31:46,605
Well, maybe
it's the best thing for her,

518
00:31:47,439 --> 00:31:48,507
for the child.

519
00:31:49,976 --> 00:31:51,177
She does know him.

520
00:31:52,144 --> 00:31:53,412
They do have a bond.

521
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:55,982
I mean, maybe she'll do better
being raised by her own.

522
00:31:56,983 --> 00:31:59,451
She's Lily-Joe's daughter.

523
00:31:59,651 --> 00:32:02,488
See, we just think
it may be easier.

524
00:32:04,323 --> 00:32:06,725
Georgia, honey,
we want what's best for you.

525
00:32:06,858 --> 00:32:09,661
Now this may be the way
out of this whole mess.

526
00:32:11,063 --> 00:32:13,199
You know how my brother
would have felt.

527
00:32:13,332 --> 00:32:15,801
I'm not interested
in how Joe would have felt.

528
00:32:18,137 --> 00:32:19,305
Thank you very much.

529
00:32:27,013 --> 00:32:29,015
Oh, that looks darling.

530
00:32:29,415 --> 00:32:31,217
-Thank you, Betty.
-Yes, ma'am.

531
00:32:31,883 --> 00:32:33,519
Now come on.
We better get going.

532
00:32:34,586 --> 00:32:36,555
You know, I could teach you
to do her hair.

533
00:32:36,688 --> 00:32:38,290
Oh, I appreciate that, Betty.

534
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:42,028
-JACEY: It's just hair.
-Well, I know.

535
00:32:42,094 --> 00:32:43,562
You know she favors you.

536
00:32:44,230 --> 00:32:47,166
-You think so?
-BETTY: She's got your eyes.

537
00:32:49,635 --> 00:32:52,304
Well, her grandfather's
taking her back to California.

538
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:55,141
Hmm.

539
00:32:55,374 --> 00:32:56,842
Sweet Creek's
an old-fashioned town

540
00:32:57,043 --> 00:32:58,777
with old-fashioned ideas.

541
00:32:59,545 --> 00:33:00,812
That sure would be easier

542
00:33:01,847 --> 00:33:03,782
if easier is what you're after.

543
00:33:05,784 --> 00:33:07,553
-I guess.
-BOTH: Bye-bye.

544
00:33:07,686 --> 00:33:09,921
-GEORGIA: Thanks again.
-Bye, Jacey.
Have a great day.

545
00:33:10,222 --> 00:33:11,857
GEORGIA: How would you like
to go to the park?

546
00:33:12,624 --> 00:33:14,560
They've got
a real nice swing there.

547
00:33:15,661 --> 00:33:17,096
You know,
I haven't been swinging

548
00:33:18,230 --> 00:33:20,866
for one, two, three, four--
a hundred years.

549
00:33:21,333 --> 00:33:22,801
-JACEY: Uh-huh.
-Uh-huh.

550
00:33:23,135 --> 00:33:25,671
Pump your legs in and out,

551
00:33:25,804 --> 00:33:27,173
in and out.

552
00:33:27,739 --> 00:33:31,277
I know how to swing.
I'm almost seven.

553
00:33:31,410 --> 00:33:32,811
You surely do.

554
00:33:33,879 --> 00:33:34,946
[*****]

555
00:33:35,581 --> 00:33:36,848
GEORGIA: You know,

556
00:33:37,416 --> 00:33:40,319
your mama used to like to swing
right up to the stars

557
00:33:40,452 --> 00:33:43,855
-and try to touch the moon.
-JACEY: That stuff's for babies.

558
00:33:44,156 --> 00:33:46,092
Swings don't really go
that high.

559
00:33:46,225 --> 00:33:48,327
GEORGIA: Well,
maybe not in California.

560
00:33:48,827 --> 00:33:51,630
But you don't have
the bilateral gravitational pull

561
00:33:51,763 --> 00:33:53,232
we have down here in the south.

562
00:33:54,266 --> 00:33:56,635
-Really?
-Uh-huh, sure.

563
00:33:58,470 --> 00:33:59,905
Okay, now lean back.

564
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:03,109
Take a deep breath.

565
00:34:04,276 --> 00:34:06,912
-Count to ten
as fast as you can.
-One, two, three, four, five,

566
00:34:07,113 --> 00:34:09,748
-six, seven, eight, nine, ten.
-Close your eyes, and take off.

567
00:34:10,716 --> 00:34:12,951
You're right.
I can see the moon.

568
00:34:13,152 --> 00:34:14,620
GEORGIA: Of course I am.

569
00:34:18,557 --> 00:34:20,259
Grandmothers know everything.

570
00:34:21,693 --> 00:34:22,928
JACEY: Higher.

571
00:34:24,130 --> 00:34:25,864
[LAUGHS]

572
00:34:29,868 --> 00:34:31,403
JACEY: I can see the moon.

573
00:34:34,873 --> 00:34:36,742
You know, having you here
in the summers

574
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:38,577
is not such a new idea.

575
00:34:39,211 --> 00:34:42,314
Your mother used to spend
summers with her grandmother.

576
00:34:43,149 --> 00:34:44,516
Maybe next summer you
and I could some time--

577
00:34:44,783 --> 00:34:47,186
On the farm with the chickens
and the cows?

578
00:34:47,319 --> 00:34:48,987
GEORGIA: Yeah.
You know about the farm?

579
00:34:49,555 --> 00:34:51,557
-JACEY: And the fountain's
outside.
-Huh.

580
00:34:51,690 --> 00:34:54,493
And you have to get up
real early to milk the cows.

581
00:34:54,626 --> 00:34:56,995
[CHUCKLES] Goodness.
Now, you know more

582
00:34:57,163 --> 00:34:59,165
about this family
than I realized.

583
00:35:00,499 --> 00:35:02,301
Were you very sick?

584
00:35:03,302 --> 00:35:04,936
No, I'm healthy as a horse, why?

585
00:35:06,071 --> 00:35:07,939
Well, mommy said...

586
00:35:09,775 --> 00:35:11,510
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

587
00:35:12,178 --> 00:35:14,246
Why don't we get us
some ice cream?

588
00:35:15,647 --> 00:35:18,484
Mommy doesn't let me
have ice cream before lunch.

589
00:35:18,717 --> 00:35:20,319
GEORGIA: Oh,
she's absolutely right.

590
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:22,621
You shouldn't have ice cream
before lunch.

591
00:35:23,322 --> 00:35:25,491
No, uh,
that was a terrible idea.

592
00:35:26,258 --> 00:35:27,926
But I have something here.

593
00:35:29,528 --> 00:35:31,930
I have something right here.

594
00:35:34,065 --> 00:35:37,102
Did you know
that saltine crackers

595
00:35:37,403 --> 00:35:39,905
are filled up with most
of the food groups

596
00:35:40,038 --> 00:35:43,275
that the FDA requires
for a healthy lunch?

597
00:35:47,646 --> 00:35:48,680
Good lunch.

598
00:35:49,315 --> 00:35:50,982
-Very good.
-[CHUCKLES]

599
00:35:51,950 --> 00:35:53,385
Let's go get some ice cream.

600
00:35:56,422 --> 00:35:57,923
Of course,
we'll finish our lunch

601
00:35:58,056 --> 00:35:59,525
before we get the ice cream.

602
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:06,898
-[*****]
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

603
00:36:07,098 --> 00:36:09,235
[WATER LAPPING]

604
00:36:11,237 --> 00:36:14,240
-GEORGIA: Thank you.
-And three boys rub the bottle,

605
00:36:14,540 --> 00:36:15,974
and the genie pops out.

606
00:36:16,508 --> 00:36:19,511
And the genie says
he'll give each boy one wish.

607
00:36:20,279 --> 00:36:22,414
The first boy wished
to be smart,

608
00:36:22,681 --> 00:36:26,252
and the genie says, "Poof,
you're smart."

609
00:36:26,385 --> 00:36:29,321
The second boy wished to be
smarter than the first boy,

610
00:36:29,455 --> 00:36:31,323
and the genie says, "Poof,

611
00:36:31,590 --> 00:36:33,392
you're smarter
than the first boy."

612
00:36:33,692 --> 00:36:35,827
And the third boy wished
to be smarter

613
00:36:35,961 --> 00:36:37,062
than the other two.

614
00:36:37,263 --> 00:36:40,466
And the genie says, "Poof,
you're a girl."

615
00:36:40,999 --> 00:36:42,501
[LAUGHS]

616
00:36:43,969 --> 00:36:45,304
You're pretty funny.

617
00:36:45,637 --> 00:36:47,306
I'm going to have write
that one down.

618
00:36:49,975 --> 00:36:52,278
Daddy says ice cream
has too much sugar.

619
00:36:52,644 --> 00:36:54,380
Your daddy was a smart man.

620
00:36:56,348 --> 00:36:58,284
He knows about all the foods.

621
00:36:58,650 --> 00:37:01,353
You have to know which foods
to keep from getting sick.

622
00:37:01,587 --> 00:37:04,155
That's right.
Did he work in the market?

623
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:07,593
No, he's a pharmacist.

624
00:37:07,726 --> 00:37:09,928
He gives you medicine
when you get too sick.

625
00:37:10,362 --> 00:37:11,663
A pharmacist.

626
00:37:12,698 --> 00:37:16,201
Well, how about your mama?
Did she work there, too?

627
00:37:16,535 --> 00:37:19,471
[CLICKS TONGUE] No.
She goes to school like me.

628
00:37:20,606 --> 00:37:21,607
To school.

629
00:37:22,641 --> 00:37:23,942
What did she study?

630
00:37:25,511 --> 00:37:26,845
Sad people.

631
00:37:30,349 --> 00:37:32,083
-GEORGIA: Hi, baby.
-Hi.

632
00:37:34,953 --> 00:37:36,355
Grandpa won't eat pie.

633
00:37:37,356 --> 00:37:38,590
More for you and me.

634
00:37:39,491 --> 00:37:43,762
* Tick tack
Right in the dough *

635
00:37:44,330 --> 00:37:48,066
* Mama bakes a pie
For Lily-Joe *

636
00:37:48,834 --> 00:37:52,338
* Mama bakes a pie
For Lily-Joe *

637
00:37:54,340 --> 00:37:55,641
Your mother taught you that?

638
00:37:56,141 --> 00:37:57,142
Yeah.

639
00:37:57,376 --> 00:38:00,045
-[DOORBELL RINGING]
-Grandpa's here.

640
00:38:12,257 --> 00:38:13,359
[SIGHS]

641
00:38:13,459 --> 00:38:15,361
JACEY: Can I please have some
more milk?

642
00:38:15,827 --> 00:38:17,195
Well, that depends.

643
00:38:18,196 --> 00:38:19,431
Are you able?

644
00:38:19,831 --> 00:38:21,967
May I please have
some more milk?

645
00:38:22,934 --> 00:38:24,370
You certainly may.

646
00:38:29,107 --> 00:38:31,543
There you go.

647
00:38:32,243 --> 00:38:34,045
-Thank you.
-LOU: You're welcome.

648
00:38:37,783 --> 00:38:39,084
[INHALES DEEPLY]

649
00:38:39,284 --> 00:38:41,820
Jacey tells me your son
was a pharmacist.

650
00:38:41,953 --> 00:38:44,289
Yeah, uh, he got his degree
at UCLA.

651
00:38:44,890 --> 00:38:46,558
GEORGIA: And Lily
was a student?

652
00:38:47,058 --> 00:38:49,661
Jacey said that she
was studying sad people.

653
00:38:51,296 --> 00:38:53,932
Oh, she was just finishing
her studies in psychology.

654
00:38:54,199 --> 00:38:55,401
GEORGIA: Really?

655
00:38:55,534 --> 00:38:57,569
I always hoped she'd go
to the University of Georgia

656
00:38:57,703 --> 00:38:59,270
when she graduated
from high school.

657
00:38:59,605 --> 00:39:00,606
Hmm.

658
00:39:02,941 --> 00:39:04,175
Uh, this is a fine dinner.

659
00:39:07,413 --> 00:39:10,616
We-- we baked a pie, but Jacey
says you won't eat it.

660
00:39:10,982 --> 00:39:13,284
No, I'm not much on deserts.

661
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:17,155
GEORGIA: Oh, honey,
Dr. Diamond called,

662
00:39:17,288 --> 00:39:19,157
and he's going to take
those old stitches out

663
00:39:19,290 --> 00:39:22,227
-tomorrow morning at 11:00 a.m.
-LOU: Dr. Diamond.

664
00:39:22,594 --> 00:39:23,795
Is he still practicing
medicine?

665
00:39:23,929 --> 00:39:25,564
One would think he'd be
retired by now.

666
00:39:25,697 --> 00:39:28,099
No, he's still going strong.
You know Dr. Diamond?

667
00:39:28,233 --> 00:39:29,267
[LAUGHS]

668
00:39:29,901 --> 00:39:32,538
Baby, he saved
your father's life

669
00:39:32,671 --> 00:39:33,905
the day he was born.

670
00:39:34,205 --> 00:39:35,441
-Really?
-LOU: Yeah, yeah.

671
00:39:35,807 --> 00:39:37,443
No other doctors would come
and visit us.

672
00:39:37,643 --> 00:39:40,479
And hospital said
it wouldn't admit patients

673
00:39:40,612 --> 00:39:42,280
who, uh, weren't pre-registered.

674
00:39:42,714 --> 00:39:44,650
We didn't have time
to go to County General.

675
00:39:44,783 --> 00:39:47,118
So your father was born
in the parking lot

676
00:39:47,252 --> 00:39:49,521
-of Mercy Hospital.
-Why?

677
00:39:49,655 --> 00:39:51,356
LOU: Because Black people
were not allowed

678
00:39:51,490 --> 00:39:52,624
in the white hospital.

679
00:39:52,758 --> 00:39:54,626
GEORGIA: That is absolutely
not true.

680
00:39:54,893 --> 00:39:56,294
And I don't think
that it is fair

681
00:39:56,462 --> 00:39:57,663
for you to fill
this child's head

682
00:39:57,796 --> 00:40:00,899
with-- with negative hateful
stories about the south.

683
00:40:01,266 --> 00:40:03,835
[SCOFFS] You're right.
Don't need to at all.

684
00:40:04,035 --> 00:40:06,304
Especially since we're leaving
tomorrow afternoon.

685
00:40:10,442 --> 00:40:12,410
Why don't we have coffee
in the living room?

686
00:40:13,211 --> 00:40:14,446
Are you ready, mademoiselle?

687
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:19,885
[WATER RUNNING]

688
00:40:20,652 --> 00:40:22,521
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

689
00:40:27,993 --> 00:40:28,994
LOU: Hi.

690
00:40:29,461 --> 00:40:30,896
I put her to bed.
I hope you don't mind.

691
00:40:31,029 --> 00:40:33,231
-No.
-She loves books.

692
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:35,300
You know,
when she was a baby,

693
00:40:35,701 --> 00:40:37,068
I started her off
on fairy tales,

694
00:40:37,202 --> 00:40:39,571
now we're moving on up
to classics. [CHUCKLES]

695
00:40:41,239 --> 00:40:42,440
You remember your first
fairy tale?

696
00:40:42,641 --> 00:40:43,842
Oh, yes, Cinderella.

697
00:40:43,975 --> 00:40:46,011
My mother must have read
it to me a hundred times.

698
00:40:46,144 --> 00:40:47,713
I remember my first
fairy tale,

699
00:40:48,246 --> 00:40:50,448
I was about Jacey's age,
about six.

700
00:40:51,049 --> 00:40:52,317
Kindergarten teacher
read it to us

701
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:55,587
on the first day of school.
Little Black Sambo.

702
00:40:57,388 --> 00:41:00,792
[SCOFFS] Is this how you intend
to raise her?

703
00:41:01,392 --> 00:41:03,562
Just filling her up
with hate and fear?

704
00:41:03,895 --> 00:41:06,097
That's part of history.
A part you don't want
to look at.

705
00:41:06,231 --> 00:41:07,432
Now, look, I don't have time
for this.

706
00:41:07,566 --> 00:41:10,068
We're leaving tomorrow,
we only have time for the truth.

707
00:41:10,201 --> 00:41:11,670
GEORGIA: Well, the truth is,

708
00:41:13,038 --> 00:41:15,106
I would be the better choice
to raise her.

709
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:17,408
Why, because you're white
or because you're a woman?

710
00:41:17,543 --> 00:41:20,045
-I am simply more appropriate.
-[GRUNTS]

711
00:41:21,580 --> 00:41:22,748
[GEORGIA GROANING]

712
00:41:26,552 --> 00:41:27,986
I know you hated my husband.

713
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:30,989
He was unspeakable
to you and to your son.

714
00:41:31,557 --> 00:41:34,159
But I am not my husband,
and I would appreciate it

715
00:41:34,292 --> 00:41:35,961
if you would not treat me
as if I were.

716
00:41:36,094 --> 00:41:38,630
He held a gun
to my son's head that night,

717
00:41:38,930 --> 00:41:40,131
and you could have stopped him.

718
00:41:40,566 --> 00:41:42,400
-You think that?
-I will take Jacey out of here

719
00:41:42,934 --> 00:41:44,135
and away from people like you,

720
00:41:44,269 --> 00:41:46,071
and there's nothing
you can do about it.

721
00:41:47,839 --> 00:41:49,808
-You know what Jacey's
handicap is?
-LOU: What?

722
00:41:49,941 --> 00:41:51,977
It's you,
and that hostile wall

723
00:41:52,110 --> 00:41:54,312
that you hide behind
to cover your own inadequacies.

724
00:41:54,713 --> 00:41:57,282
I may be inadequate,
but I didn't chase my only child

725
00:41:57,415 --> 00:41:58,584
out of my life.

726
00:41:59,150 --> 00:42:01,219
[*****]

727
00:42:03,088 --> 00:42:04,590
[DOOR OPENING, CLOSING]

728
00:42:09,761 --> 00:42:11,630
GEORGIA: Jacey, breakfast.

729
00:42:16,768 --> 00:42:19,237
Honey? Breakfast.

730
00:42:27,078 --> 00:42:30,782
-What are you doing, baby?
-I'm trying to look like Mommy.

731
00:42:31,717 --> 00:42:32,718
Oh.

732
00:42:34,252 --> 00:42:36,321
Well, honey,
you do look like Mommy.

733
00:42:37,355 --> 00:42:40,125
But mostly you look
just like you.

734
00:42:41,259 --> 00:42:43,662
I'm sorry I don't have
the same skin

735
00:42:43,795 --> 00:42:45,163
as you and Mommy.

736
00:42:46,865 --> 00:42:49,100
Why would you say
something like that?

737
00:42:49,768 --> 00:42:51,703
Because we're going so far away.

738
00:42:52,871 --> 00:42:55,406
And Grandpa said
it would be easier for you

739
00:42:55,540 --> 00:42:58,443
to remember me
if I had white skin.

740
00:42:59,210 --> 00:43:03,314
[SNIFFLES, SIGHS]
Well, your grandpa is wrong.

741
00:43:04,282 --> 00:43:08,519
I would never forget you.
Never in a million years.

742
00:43:09,287 --> 00:43:11,522
You're my grandbaby,
you hear me?

743
00:43:12,891 --> 00:43:15,293
Mommy told me her mom
was too sick

744
00:43:15,426 --> 00:43:16,662
to be a grandma.

745
00:43:18,664 --> 00:43:20,699
[INHALES DEEPLY]
Well, maybe I was.

746
00:43:23,068 --> 00:43:24,269
But I'm getting better.

747
00:43:27,372 --> 00:43:29,107
It sure was nice
getting to know you,

748
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:31,009
even if just for a little bit.

749
00:43:31,843 --> 00:43:33,845
Maybe you'll come see me
sometime.

750
00:43:34,780 --> 00:43:35,781
JACEY: Maybe.

751
00:43:36,848 --> 00:43:42,253
GEORGIA: Let's see now,
seven, six, here we are.

752
00:43:52,397 --> 00:43:54,232
Mr. Hastings, are you in there?

753
00:43:57,368 --> 00:43:58,436
[CHUCKLES]

754
00:43:58,569 --> 00:44:00,238
Maybe he went to breakfast
or something.

755
00:44:01,472 --> 00:44:02,507
Let's go see.

756
00:44:07,879 --> 00:44:10,048
Oh, my God. Help!

757
00:44:10,615 --> 00:44:11,950
Help! We need some help here!

758
00:44:12,751 --> 00:44:14,485
-WOMAN: Yes, ma'am.
-GEORGIA: Can you unlock
this door, please?

759
00:44:14,619 --> 00:44:15,821
WOMAN: Yes, ma'am.

760
00:44:19,290 --> 00:44:21,492
-Oh. Come on.
-WOMAN: I'll get
the manager, ma'am.

761
00:44:24,763 --> 00:44:25,931
OPERATOR: 911,
what is your emergency?

762
00:44:26,064 --> 00:44:27,298
-This is an emergency.
-OPERATOR: Yes.

763
00:44:27,432 --> 00:44:30,001
Please send an ambulance
to the motel on Cherry Street.

764
00:44:30,135 --> 00:44:31,737
Is Grandpa sick again?

765
00:44:33,404 --> 00:44:34,472
Again?

766
00:44:35,640 --> 00:44:37,108
Honey, he's been sick before?

767
00:44:38,076 --> 00:44:39,277
OPERATOR: Ma'am?

768
00:44:39,745 --> 00:44:42,613
Ma'am, this is 911.
How can I help you, ma'am?

769
00:44:44,983 --> 00:44:47,285
DR. ROSE: Hi, I'm Dr. Rose.
Are you here with Mr. Hastings?

770
00:44:47,418 --> 00:44:49,354
-Yes.
-DR. ROSE: He's going
to be fine.

771
00:44:49,755 --> 00:44:51,957
He took too much insulin,
and his blood sugar got too low.

772
00:44:52,090 --> 00:44:53,925
But we managed to revive
him rather quickly.

773
00:44:54,192 --> 00:44:57,395
-He's a diabetic?
-Yes. I thought you knew that.

774
00:44:58,496 --> 00:45:00,398
Well, then,
he isn't a drug addict.

775
00:45:01,366 --> 00:45:04,169
No. We can't release him alone.

776
00:45:04,302 --> 00:45:06,471
He's not very
well-controlled right now.

777
00:45:06,604 --> 00:45:08,373
And he has a severe foot ulcer.

778
00:45:08,774 --> 00:45:10,241
And he told us he was
in a California hospital

779
00:45:10,375 --> 00:45:12,010
for treatment,
but he checked out
a few days ago.

780
00:45:12,677 --> 00:45:14,780
-Mm. To come here.
-Yeah.

781
00:45:14,913 --> 00:45:17,115
Well, his kidneys and heart
are doing fine right now.

782
00:45:17,248 --> 00:45:19,150
But we've got to get
his sugars under control.

783
00:45:19,785 --> 00:45:21,853
The important thing
is keeping his wound clean

784
00:45:21,987 --> 00:45:23,989
and medicated
or he could lose his foot.

785
00:45:24,422 --> 00:45:25,590
GEORGIA: My word.

786
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:29,227
-Does your foot hurt?
-No, I don't feel a thing.

787
00:45:30,628 --> 00:45:31,897
-How are you?
-Oh, I'm fine.

788
00:45:32,030 --> 00:45:34,165
Now, this never happens,
you know, except for the travel

789
00:45:34,299 --> 00:45:36,101
and the stress and me
not being careful,

790
00:45:36,467 --> 00:45:37,635
it'll never happen again.

791
00:45:38,303 --> 00:45:39,337
And I still plan

792
00:45:39,470 --> 00:45:41,907
to take little Jacey
back to San Diego.

793
00:45:43,074 --> 00:45:44,810
I called over
to the resident care center.

794
00:45:44,943 --> 00:45:46,878
I'm going to have you moved
over there tomorrow.

795
00:45:47,012 --> 00:45:49,614
Thank you. Two weeks.

796
00:45:50,481 --> 00:45:51,616
That's all I need.

797
00:45:51,950 --> 00:45:53,651
Then I'll get home get back
on my schedule and everything's

798
00:45:53,819 --> 00:45:55,053
going to be better.
[INHALES SHARPLY]

799
00:45:55,186 --> 00:45:56,187
Come here, little bear.

800
00:45:58,123 --> 00:45:59,958
You are gonna have to stay
with your grandma for a while

801
00:46:00,091 --> 00:46:01,426
until I get better, okay?

802
00:46:01,659 --> 00:46:04,229
-No, you can stay with us
in my room.
-Oh, no, no, no.

803
00:46:04,362 --> 00:46:05,730
-I'll take care of you.
-I can't do that.

804
00:46:05,864 --> 00:46:07,132
-Why not?
-No, I just can't.

805
00:46:07,265 --> 00:46:09,667
I want to be with you.
Please don't leave me with her.

806
00:46:09,835 --> 00:46:12,437
No, no. Listen to me now.
Listen to me.

807
00:46:13,304 --> 00:46:16,842
Time is going to fly by so fast.
[CHUCKLES]

808
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:18,443
You'll stay with us.

809
00:46:19,845 --> 00:46:21,146
Until you're on your feet.

810
00:46:22,914 --> 00:46:26,117
Jacey wants you nearby,
and I want what Jacey wants.

811
00:46:26,451 --> 00:46:29,554
I don't think
that that would be possible.

812
00:46:29,955 --> 00:46:32,723
Why? Because I'm a woman
or because I'm white?

813
00:46:36,427 --> 00:46:37,495
You're kidding me, right?

814
00:46:38,096 --> 00:46:39,931
You're going to have
that man living with you

815
00:46:40,065 --> 00:46:41,967
in your home?
Are you crazy?

816
00:46:42,333 --> 00:46:45,403
Madeleine, she lost both
her mother and her father.

817
00:46:45,703 --> 00:46:46,872
She can't lose him too.

818
00:46:46,972 --> 00:46:49,207
Oh, my God, Georgia.
Send him a card.

819
00:46:49,474 --> 00:46:50,608
Make him a pie.

820
00:46:50,909 --> 00:46:53,411
You don't invite a man
like that into your home.

821
00:46:53,544 --> 00:46:54,980
A man like what?

822
00:46:55,246 --> 00:46:56,681
Don't you play games
with me.

823
00:46:57,348 --> 00:46:58,884
You are a single woman
living alone

824
00:46:59,017 --> 00:47:00,118
in a town that has

825
00:47:01,352 --> 00:47:04,890
-formalities and traditions.
-Well, the hell with the town.

826
00:47:05,190 --> 00:47:06,724
I-- I got to do what's right
for her.

827
00:47:07,125 --> 00:47:09,327
It's one thing to have
a beautiful Black baby

828
00:47:09,460 --> 00:47:10,561
living in your house.

829
00:47:10,795 --> 00:47:12,697
It's another to have
a fully-grown Black man

830
00:47:12,898 --> 00:47:14,232
sleeping under your roof.

831
00:47:14,900 --> 00:47:16,434
And you have a choice here.

832
00:47:18,469 --> 00:47:21,139
No, I don't have a choice.

833
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:25,176
I need to do what's best
for Jacey.

834
00:47:27,745 --> 00:47:30,181
[FLIES BUZZING]

835
00:47:32,150 --> 00:47:34,119
-LOU: Now, this is your room.
-Yes, it is.

836
00:47:34,619 --> 00:47:36,154
This is not right.
I need to find another room.

837
00:47:36,287 --> 00:47:38,823
All the rest of the bedrooms
are upstairs.

838
00:47:39,224 --> 00:47:40,491
This room is perfect.

839
00:47:40,959 --> 00:47:42,961
The bathroom is right
across the hall.

840
00:47:43,428 --> 00:47:45,964
-It'll be easier for you.
-I won't take your room.

841
00:47:46,531 --> 00:47:47,832
It's already done.

842
00:47:48,733 --> 00:47:52,003
I moved all my things upstairs
so that I can be closer

843
00:47:52,137 --> 00:47:53,138
to Jacey.

844
00:47:53,604 --> 00:47:54,705
You will stay in here,

845
00:47:54,839 --> 00:47:56,374
and there's nothing
you can do about it.

846
00:47:57,008 --> 00:47:58,977
I think she's mad at you.

847
00:48:01,279 --> 00:48:04,282
[*****]

848
00:48:06,484 --> 00:48:07,752
[CHUCKLES]

849
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:11,156
-MIDGE: Hey, Mrs. Porter.
-[BARKS]

850
00:48:11,289 --> 00:48:13,858
-GEORGIA: Hi, Max.
-MIDGE: Oh. oops, I better go.

851
00:48:13,992 --> 00:48:16,861
I don't think that Max
likes Smoky Number Two
very much.

852
00:48:17,262 --> 00:48:19,164
He just needs to get
to know her.

853
00:48:19,664 --> 00:48:20,765
Mommy said that animals

854
00:48:20,966 --> 00:48:22,500
think they hate
different animals,

855
00:48:22,633 --> 00:48:25,236
but they're just afraid to love
what they don't know.

856
00:48:25,636 --> 00:48:26,671
[MEOWS]

857
00:48:29,774 --> 00:48:31,542
Your mama was a smart cookie.

858
00:48:34,879 --> 00:48:36,414
-[DOOR KNOCKING]
-Come in.

859
00:48:37,715 --> 00:48:39,084
Supper is served.

860
00:48:39,484 --> 00:48:41,252
It's early,
but we Southern ladies

861
00:48:41,386 --> 00:48:43,221
supper early in the south.

862
00:48:43,354 --> 00:48:45,323
-[LAUGHS]
-Absolutely right.

863
00:48:45,523 --> 00:48:48,493
Now you remember you was born
and raised in California.

864
00:48:49,294 --> 00:48:51,496
-I made the rice and the salad.
-Mm.

865
00:48:53,098 --> 00:48:55,000
Don't eat the slimy stuff.

866
00:48:55,133 --> 00:48:57,002
GEORGIA: Oh, your grandpa
was raised down here.

867
00:48:57,102 --> 00:48:58,469
I bet he just loves okra.

868
00:48:58,603 --> 00:48:59,870
[SCOFFS] I may have
grown up here,

869
00:49:00,005 --> 00:49:02,373
but you're right,
that okra is a vile substitute

870
00:49:02,507 --> 00:49:03,774
for a vegetable.

871
00:49:04,209 --> 00:49:05,910
-[LAUGHS]
-GEORGIA: Honey,
why don't you run

872
00:49:06,044 --> 00:49:08,179
and get the salt and pepper?
I forgot 'em.

873
00:49:17,755 --> 00:49:21,926
Look, if this little charade
is an attempt to coerce me

874
00:49:22,060 --> 00:49:24,029
into letting Jacey stay here
in Sweet Creek,

875
00:49:25,030 --> 00:49:26,131
you're wrong.

876
00:49:26,397 --> 00:49:27,798
I'm going to fight you
all the way.

877
00:49:27,932 --> 00:49:30,335
I know. You have told me
several times.

878
00:49:31,436 --> 00:49:32,903
You know, I am trying
to be civil

879
00:49:33,038 --> 00:49:35,106
in a very
uncomfortable situation.

880
00:49:35,473 --> 00:49:37,208
I would appreciate it
if you would extend me

881
00:49:37,342 --> 00:49:40,411
-the same courtesy.
-Look, you and I,

882
00:49:40,545 --> 00:49:41,912
we may have grown up here,

883
00:49:42,380 --> 00:49:43,648
but we come
from different worlds.

884
00:49:43,781 --> 00:49:45,216
GEORGIA: Mr. Hastings,

885
00:49:45,783 --> 00:49:49,820
you just lost your son,
and I just lost my daughter.

886
00:49:50,321 --> 00:49:53,358
We live in the same world
whether we like it or not.

887
00:49:54,959 --> 00:49:56,061
LOU: Mrs. Porter...

888
00:49:58,063 --> 00:49:59,164
tomorrow's Jacey's birthday.

889
00:49:59,297 --> 00:50:00,898
Now, Lily used to make
her a cake.

890
00:50:01,132 --> 00:50:02,800
Now, will you get her
one tomorrow, please?

891
00:50:03,834 --> 00:50:06,304
-No chocolate.
-Makes her throw up. I know.

892
00:50:08,606 --> 00:50:09,940
-Thank you.
-GEORGIA: You're welcome.

893
00:50:14,279 --> 00:50:16,013
You roll on over there.

894
00:50:17,082 --> 00:50:18,216
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

895
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:22,053
Why do you have stars up there?

896
00:50:23,121 --> 00:50:25,523
Those are your mother's stars.

897
00:50:27,458 --> 00:50:29,860
You know, there's one there
for every year of her life.

898
00:50:30,861 --> 00:50:32,630
Your mama just loved stars.

899
00:50:34,232 --> 00:50:38,169
Do you think Mommy and Daddy
miss me as much as I miss them?

900
00:50:38,703 --> 00:50:40,338
No, ma'am, I do not.

901
00:50:41,072 --> 00:50:44,109
I think your mother and father
are right here watching

902
00:50:44,242 --> 00:50:45,410
over you.

903
00:50:45,643 --> 00:50:46,811
They're making sure
you're happy,

904
00:50:46,944 --> 00:50:48,879
and they're making sure
you're not eating

905
00:50:49,013 --> 00:50:50,181
too much ice cream.

906
00:50:51,149 --> 00:50:54,852
So, you just better go to sleep
and give them some rest.

907
00:50:55,620 --> 00:50:59,290
[*****]

908
00:51:01,926 --> 00:51:03,728
Roses on your pillow.

909
00:51:06,297 --> 00:51:07,965
Roses on your pillow, honey.

910
00:51:41,065 --> 00:51:42,167
[CHUCKLES]

911
00:51:45,503 --> 00:51:46,937
LOU: Feminine Mystique.

912
00:51:50,508 --> 00:51:52,777
The Woman's Struggle
Against Man.

913
00:51:56,514 --> 00:51:59,016
Alone and Happy.
No, no, no, no.

914
00:52:00,418 --> 00:52:01,652
A Woman's Guide.

915
00:52:02,320 --> 00:52:03,521
Hmm.

916
00:52:06,557 --> 00:52:09,427
"There is a warrior
in every one of us.

917
00:52:10,195 --> 00:52:11,962
A woman will call
on her warrior

918
00:52:12,197 --> 00:52:13,498
or let her sleep."

919
00:52:14,098 --> 00:52:16,701
[*****]

920
00:52:17,468 --> 00:52:18,736
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

921
00:52:26,110 --> 00:52:27,512
What am I doing here?

922
00:52:28,579 --> 00:52:29,847
GEORGIA: Meet your approval?

923
00:52:31,048 --> 00:52:32,116
It's just fine.

924
00:52:32,783 --> 00:52:34,852
Yeah, it's not bad.

925
00:52:36,086 --> 00:52:37,288
I called Madeleine
this morning,

926
00:52:37,422 --> 00:52:39,557
and I asked her to invite
her grandchildren over

927
00:52:39,690 --> 00:52:41,226
to the Georgia Peach meeting.

928
00:52:41,392 --> 00:52:43,228
That way Jacey will meet
some friends,

929
00:52:43,328 --> 00:52:44,862
and then I'll invite them
back here for cake

930
00:52:44,995 --> 00:52:47,232
-and ice cream later.
-Just what is a Georgia Peach?

931
00:52:47,432 --> 00:52:50,235
They're, uh, a group
of women volunteers.

932
00:52:50,435 --> 00:52:52,570
Currently we're putting
on a dinner to raise money

933
00:52:52,703 --> 00:52:54,539
-for the homeless shelter.
-LOU: Hmm.

934
00:52:55,005 --> 00:52:56,574
Well, Lily volunteered
for the battered woman shelter

935
00:52:56,707 --> 00:52:58,108
-in San Diego.
-Did she?

936
00:52:58,343 --> 00:52:59,344
LOU: Mm.

937
00:53:00,711 --> 00:53:01,812
Thank you for telling me.

938
00:53:02,947 --> 00:53:05,883
-Thank you for the cake.
-[INHALES] I did it for Jacey.

939
00:53:10,888 --> 00:53:12,423
-BETTY: Hello, Jacey.
Hello, Mrs. Porter.
-GEORGIA: Hi.

940
00:53:12,890 --> 00:53:16,261
-How are you, Betty?
-Hello, Jacey. Happy birthday.

941
00:53:16,394 --> 00:53:17,728
JACEY: Thank you.

942
00:53:17,962 --> 00:53:20,130
Oh, she's so excited
to be meeting
your grandchildren.

943
00:53:20,265 --> 00:53:22,633
I'm so sorry,
but the girls couldn't come.

944
00:53:22,767 --> 00:53:25,035
-They have the sniffles.
-Aw.

945
00:53:25,536 --> 00:53:26,604
All three of them?

946
00:53:27,838 --> 00:53:28,906
That's too bad.

947
00:53:29,039 --> 00:53:30,941
Well, Jacey,
you're just going to have to be

948
00:53:31,075 --> 00:53:32,410
a Georgia Peach today.

949
00:53:32,910 --> 00:53:35,946
You sit right beside me
and all my good friends.

950
00:53:37,682 --> 00:53:38,783
MADELEINE: Well, I think
we should move

951
00:53:38,916 --> 00:53:40,418
right to the first order
of business.

952
00:53:41,085 --> 00:53:43,288
I spoke to the caterer,
and she said

953
00:53:43,388 --> 00:53:45,890
that the three main orders
would be more than enough

954
00:53:46,291 --> 00:53:48,726
so that we should cancel
the caviar and toast.

955
00:53:48,926 --> 00:53:50,961
Now right there
we'll save 800 dollars.

956
00:53:51,095 --> 00:53:52,297
GEORGIA: Wonderful.

957
00:53:53,097 --> 00:53:56,100
Oh, my word,
Betty made her shortcake.

958
00:53:56,434 --> 00:53:58,503
Half the reason people
come to the gala

959
00:53:58,636 --> 00:54:00,905
is to try some
of Betty's great deserts.

960
00:54:01,339 --> 00:54:04,342
And to see what racy
thing I might wear.

961
00:54:04,609 --> 00:54:05,810
MADELEINE: Better start
baking now, Betty.

962
00:54:05,943 --> 00:54:08,012
Looks like we're going
to have a big turnout.

963
00:54:08,313 --> 00:54:11,215
-Yes, ma'am.
-GEORGIA: Betty, you've been
as much a part

964
00:54:11,349 --> 00:54:13,418
of the Georgia Peaches
as any one of us.

965
00:54:14,419 --> 00:54:16,321
We should make you
an honorary Peach.

966
00:54:20,157 --> 00:54:21,426
Well, that's true enough.

967
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:25,062
-My Betty's a special girl.
-Thank you, ma'am.

968
00:54:26,364 --> 00:54:28,866
-Thank you, Miss Porter.
-My goodness, Betty.

969
00:54:28,999 --> 00:54:32,169
We've known each other 15 years.
Please call me Georgia.

970
00:54:33,571 --> 00:54:34,739
Thank you, ma'am.

971
00:54:35,573 --> 00:54:36,574
Georgia.

972
00:54:37,041 --> 00:54:39,677
Betty, I think I'll take
an itsy-bitsy piece

973
00:54:39,810 --> 00:54:40,878
of that cake now.

974
00:54:45,983 --> 00:54:48,953
Such a shame the gardens
aren't as nice as last year.

975
00:54:50,755 --> 00:54:52,156
[EXHALES DEEPLY]
What is with you?

976
00:54:52,823 --> 00:54:54,024
GEORGIA: Me?
What's with you?

977
00:54:54,492 --> 00:54:55,960
[SCOFFS] All
of your grandchildren

978
00:54:56,093 --> 00:54:57,695
are suddenly unavailable.

979
00:54:58,563 --> 00:55:02,199
That is just-- that's bull.
That's what it is.

980
00:55:03,901 --> 00:55:05,770
You have a Black man
living in your home.

981
00:55:05,903 --> 00:55:07,838
Now isn't that just a slap
in the face?

982
00:55:08,138 --> 00:55:09,474
Why? He's not living
in your home.

983
00:55:10,107 --> 00:55:11,241
Don't you dare.

984
00:55:11,909 --> 00:55:13,611
I treat Betty like a member
of my family.

985
00:55:13,744 --> 00:55:16,814
I always have.
But there are rules.

986
00:55:17,548 --> 00:55:19,850
I know where the line is
and you have crossed it.

987
00:55:20,284 --> 00:55:21,986
Maybe it's time
we moved the line.

988
00:55:22,920 --> 00:55:25,255
As a matter of fact,
I'm thinking of asking

989
00:55:25,390 --> 00:55:28,793
Lou Hastings to be my escort
to the Georgia Peach dinner.

990
00:55:28,926 --> 00:55:30,528
Are you trying to provoke me?

991
00:55:30,661 --> 00:55:33,698
This is not about you.
This is about Jacey.

992
00:55:34,765 --> 00:55:36,834
She's part
of your family now, too.

993
00:55:37,635 --> 00:55:39,570
And it's time you started
treating her like that.

994
00:55:39,704 --> 00:55:41,005
You self-righteous--

995
00:55:42,272 --> 00:55:43,974
I love you like a sister,

996
00:55:44,809 --> 00:55:46,110
and I am sorry about Lily,

997
00:55:46,243 --> 00:55:49,580
but don't you preach to me.
You were me a week ago.

998
00:55:51,516 --> 00:55:52,917
Then shame on me.

999
00:55:59,590 --> 00:56:01,726
-Hi, Grandpa.
-LOU: Hey, little bear.

1000
00:56:03,461 --> 00:56:05,763
-The kids weren't there.
-Aw.

1001
00:56:07,297 --> 00:56:09,800
This town has changed, huh?
I should have known better.

1002
00:56:09,934 --> 00:56:11,001
They were sick.

1003
00:56:11,135 --> 00:56:12,437
It didn't have anything
to do with anything.

1004
00:56:13,438 --> 00:56:15,105
Don't you worry
about those kids, little bear.

1005
00:56:15,906 --> 00:56:18,443
I've got a very special
birthday gift just for you.

1006
00:56:21,211 --> 00:56:22,713
-Look at that.
-JACEY

1007
00:56:22,847 --> 00:56:24,549
It looks just like Mommy's.

1008
00:56:24,682 --> 00:56:26,751
Well, it is Mommy's.
She wanted you to have it.

1009
00:56:27,151 --> 00:56:28,786
JACEY: I'm going to go show
Smoky Number Two.

1010
00:56:28,919 --> 00:56:29,920
All right.

1011
00:56:31,956 --> 00:56:34,459
I gave that cross to Lily
for her confirmation

1012
00:56:34,525 --> 00:56:36,060
when she was 12 years old.

1013
00:56:36,193 --> 00:56:38,829
[*****]

1014
00:56:39,029 --> 00:56:40,197
Yeah.

1015
00:56:41,165 --> 00:56:42,132
Oh.

1016
00:56:42,600 --> 00:56:44,669
Here, we got you
some books.

1017
00:56:45,335 --> 00:56:47,538
Did you know
that two of the authors

1018
00:56:47,672 --> 00:56:49,139
on the best-selling list
are Black--

1019
00:56:49,807 --> 00:56:52,910
-I mean African-American?
-Does that surprise you?

1020
00:56:53,143 --> 00:56:55,480
Yeah, it does.
Maybe I'm growing.

1021
00:56:55,746 --> 00:56:58,248
I wouldn't worry about it.
You've got a lot to overcome.

1022
00:57:00,150 --> 00:57:01,151
Try it.

1023
00:57:05,089 --> 00:57:07,692
-There.
-Well, thank you.

1024
00:57:07,958 --> 00:57:10,728
-That's been broken a long time.
-Well, you're welcome.

1025
00:57:11,128 --> 00:57:12,262
It's the least I could do.

1026
00:57:12,530 --> 00:57:14,765
I know how hard it was for you
to take me in.

1027
00:57:16,200 --> 00:57:17,367
Why you got so many catalogs?

1028
00:57:17,635 --> 00:57:19,036
Oh, I just like to shop at home.

1029
00:57:19,970 --> 00:57:22,206
I like to be able to think
without a salesperson

1030
00:57:22,339 --> 00:57:23,373
standing over me.

1031
00:57:23,508 --> 00:57:24,809
You probably wouldn't
understand that.

1032
00:57:24,942 --> 00:57:26,043
You're so good with people.

1033
00:57:29,179 --> 00:57:30,147
Oh.

1034
00:57:30,515 --> 00:57:31,516
What?

1035
00:57:31,782 --> 00:57:34,585
Oh, I didn't even know
it was July.

1036
00:57:35,052 --> 00:57:36,821
-What is it?
-Oh.

1037
00:57:38,923 --> 00:57:43,528
Once a year, the Star Registry
sells ownership of the stars.

1038
00:57:44,328 --> 00:57:46,564
You get to name them
and keep them forever.

1039
00:57:47,865 --> 00:57:50,167
I bought one every year
since Lily...

1040
00:57:52,269 --> 00:57:53,403
you know, went away.

1041
00:57:54,438 --> 00:57:55,706
They publish her name
and mine

1042
00:57:55,840 --> 00:57:58,676
in every important newspaper
all over the country.

1043
00:57:59,544 --> 00:58:02,547
And I-- I just always hoped
that wherever she was,

1044
00:58:02,613 --> 00:58:04,782
she might-- she might see
our names

1045
00:58:04,915 --> 00:58:06,917
and-- and know
how much I love her.

1046
00:58:09,654 --> 00:58:12,557
She could call the registry too,
and they'd send her, her stars.

1047
00:58:12,990 --> 00:58:14,725
You know, they
were just little charms

1048
00:58:14,859 --> 00:58:16,160
for bracelets.

1049
00:58:17,461 --> 00:58:19,196
Oh, I guess this is stupid.

1050
00:58:19,697 --> 00:58:24,068
[*****]

1051
00:58:25,936 --> 00:58:27,337
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1052
00:58:31,208 --> 00:58:32,577
-GEORGIA: Hi, Betty.
-BETTY: Hi.

1053
00:58:32,677 --> 00:58:35,479
I brought my grandchildren over
for Jacey's birthday party.

1054
00:58:36,847 --> 00:58:38,683
Um, I'm sorry,
maybe I should have called.

1055
00:58:38,816 --> 00:58:40,951
Oh, no, that's wonderful.
Jacey.

1056
00:58:41,418 --> 00:58:43,854
No, come on in.
I'm so happy to see you.

1057
00:58:43,988 --> 00:58:46,991
-BETTY: Thank you.
-Hi, I'm Jacey. I'm seven.

1058
00:58:47,124 --> 00:58:47,992
-GIRL: Hello.
-BOY: Hi.

1059
00:58:48,125 --> 00:58:49,226
Are those for me?

1060
00:58:50,027 --> 00:58:51,295
-GIRL: Happy birthday.
-JACEY: Thank you.

1061
00:58:51,428 --> 00:58:52,597
-[CHUCKLES]
-BOY: Happy birthday, Jacey.

1062
00:58:52,663 --> 00:58:53,698
JACEY: You wanna come see
my room?

1063
00:58:53,831 --> 00:58:55,499
-GIRL: That'll be great.
-BOY: Sure.

1064
00:58:56,601 --> 00:58:58,168
-Oh, thank you.
-You're welcome.

1065
00:58:58,302 --> 00:58:59,604
I'll pick them up
in a couple of hours.

1066
00:58:59,737 --> 00:59:01,205
GEORGIA: Oh, come on in
and stay for dinner.

1067
00:59:01,939 --> 00:59:03,173
-Are you sure?
-GEORGIA: Hey.

1068
00:59:03,307 --> 00:59:06,376
-We got birthday cake here.
-Oh, in that case.

1069
00:59:06,510 --> 00:59:08,112
[BOTH LAUGH]

1070
00:59:08,345 --> 00:59:09,714
-Hello.
-This is Lou Hastings.

1071
00:59:09,914 --> 00:59:10,915
Hi.

1072
00:59:11,148 --> 00:59:13,718
Lou, this is Betty Greenlee,
my friend.

1073
00:59:14,451 --> 00:59:16,186
-Pleasure to meet you.
-The pleasure is all mine.

1074
00:59:16,453 --> 00:59:17,487
Come on.

1075
00:59:18,355 --> 00:59:19,489
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1076
00:59:22,092 --> 00:59:24,161
-GEORGIA: Ellen.
-Is this where the party is?

1077
00:59:24,294 --> 00:59:26,263
It sure is.
How are you, girls?

1078
00:59:26,697 --> 00:59:28,666
The other kids are upstairs.
Why don't you all go up?

1079
00:59:28,799 --> 00:59:30,067
-[KID LAUGHING]
-Come on in.

1080
00:59:31,268 --> 00:59:32,469
-ELLEN: Hi.
-Hello.

1081
00:59:34,338 --> 00:59:37,307
-Just an illusion, huh?
-[SCOFFS] Smoke and mirrors.

1082
00:59:38,108 --> 00:59:39,309
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
-[LOU LAUGHING]

1083
00:59:39,443 --> 00:59:40,978
All right, here we go
with the birthday cake.

1084
00:59:41,111 --> 00:59:42,647
Oh, here it comes.

1085
00:59:42,747 --> 00:59:44,248
-LOU: Birthday cake coming
right now.
-It's getting closer.

1086
00:59:44,381 --> 00:59:47,785
-Here it comes.
-[ALL CHEER]

1087
00:59:47,918 --> 00:59:49,386
GEORGIA: Okay,
blow them all out.

1088
00:59:49,654 --> 00:59:51,521
-One, two--
-Don't forget to make a wish.

1089
00:59:52,823 --> 00:59:53,824
GEORGIA: Three.

1090
00:59:56,126 --> 00:59:57,294
LOU: Oh, yeah.

1091
00:59:57,427 --> 00:59:59,730
-[ALL CHEER AND APPLAUSE]
-What did you wish?

1092
01:00:01,398 --> 01:00:04,835
I can't say it
or it won't come true.

1093
01:00:08,939 --> 01:00:11,508
They're here, little bear.
They are right here.

1094
01:00:13,143 --> 01:00:15,980
-Happy birthday, honey.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1095
01:00:16,480 --> 01:00:18,783
-I want a big piece.
-LOU: You want a big piece?

1096
01:00:18,916 --> 01:00:20,851
[ALL LAUGH]

1097
01:00:20,985 --> 01:00:22,386
LOU: I'm going to have
a big piece, okay?

1098
01:00:22,519 --> 01:00:23,921
I'm eating the whole
cake right now.

1099
01:00:24,822 --> 01:00:25,990
[ALL LAUGH]

1100
01:00:34,164 --> 01:00:35,265
LOU: Bye-bye, girls.

1101
01:00:36,533 --> 01:00:38,268
Goodbye, girls. Y'all come back.

1102
01:00:39,804 --> 01:00:41,138
-Nice meeting you.
-All right.

1103
01:00:41,906 --> 01:00:44,942
-Thank you for coming, Ellen.
-Oh, my pleasure.

1104
01:00:46,043 --> 01:00:48,112
That is one handsome man.

1105
01:00:48,478 --> 01:00:50,614
I'd have the vapors knowing
he was sleeping right there

1106
01:00:50,748 --> 01:00:52,883
-under my roof.
-What are you talking about?

1107
01:00:53,017 --> 01:00:55,419
ELLEN: Oh, please, Georgia.
Grow up.

1108
01:00:55,652 --> 01:00:56,721
This may be the south,

1109
01:00:56,854 --> 01:00:59,356
but you'd have to be
dead not to notice him.

1110
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:00,991
Well, I assure you I don't.

1111
01:01:05,763 --> 01:01:06,764
Bye.

1112
01:01:16,974 --> 01:01:18,142
LOU: Oh, that was
a great party.

1113
01:01:18,275 --> 01:01:19,343
JACEY: Yeah.

1114
01:01:19,476 --> 01:01:20,745
LOU: Don't you worry,
little bear.

1115
01:01:20,811 --> 01:01:22,747
Soon we'll be home
and everything will be back

1116
01:01:22,813 --> 01:01:23,814
to normal.

1117
01:01:25,249 --> 01:01:26,283
Hey, maybe...

1118
01:01:27,584 --> 01:01:29,286
we'll have one of those
end-of-the-summer parties,

1119
01:01:29,419 --> 01:01:30,587
the way we had last year.

1120
01:01:31,088 --> 01:01:33,090
-Okay?
-When we ran in the sprinkler

1121
01:01:33,223 --> 01:01:35,760
-and ate popsicles?
-Absolutely. Sure.

1122
01:01:35,960 --> 01:01:39,263
JACEY: Remember what Daddy did
on my birthday when I was three?

1123
01:01:39,764 --> 01:01:41,766
LOU: Oh, yeah, he--
he woke you up

1124
01:01:41,866 --> 01:01:43,834
in the middle of the night
and drove you to the beach

1125
01:01:43,968 --> 01:01:46,036
and built a bonfire
in the sand, right?

1126
01:01:46,170 --> 01:01:48,472
And we chased fireflies
and roasted marshmallows.

1127
01:01:48,605 --> 01:01:49,974
[LAUGHS] Yeah.

1128
01:01:50,540 --> 01:01:53,110
You were such a baby.
How can you remember that?

1129
01:01:55,880 --> 01:01:57,681
It's my best day with Daddy.

1130
01:02:00,250 --> 01:02:01,351
Yeah.

1131
01:02:03,020 --> 01:02:05,089
LOU: Well, anyway,
you, uh, close your eyes

1132
01:02:05,222 --> 01:02:07,057
and dream about being home.

1133
01:02:08,525 --> 01:02:11,061
-What about Grandma?
-LOU: What about Grandma?

1134
01:02:11,195 --> 01:02:12,963
JACEY: Is she coming with us?

1135
01:02:13,097 --> 01:02:15,365
[*****]

1136
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:17,067
Well, see...

1137
01:02:19,003 --> 01:02:22,106
y-- your grandma,
she has a whole life here.

1138
01:02:22,940 --> 01:02:24,408
This is her home.

1139
01:02:25,409 --> 01:02:27,845
She wouldn't enjoy California
the way we do.

1140
01:02:28,512 --> 01:02:30,680
Besides where would
she find all those catalogs?

1141
01:02:31,115 --> 01:02:33,083
Hmm? [LAUGHS]

1142
01:02:34,118 --> 01:02:36,253
All right, close your eyes
and get some sleep.

1143
01:02:37,121 --> 01:02:40,290
-Butterfly kiss.
-Butterfly kiss? Okay.

1144
01:02:44,094 --> 01:02:46,163
-Eskimo kiss?
-Eskimo kiss, too.

1145
01:02:49,333 --> 01:02:51,601
-Night, Grandpa.
-Night, little bear.

1146
01:02:51,735 --> 01:02:56,006
[*****]

1147
01:03:05,950 --> 01:03:07,017
[CAT MEOWS]

1148
01:03:10,754 --> 01:03:11,755
LOU: Oh.

1149
01:03:12,422 --> 01:03:13,557
Sorry, I didn't know
you were in here.

1150
01:03:13,690 --> 01:03:16,593
I just, uh, come
to get some water.

1151
01:03:22,766 --> 01:03:24,434
Smoky Number One was with her

1152
01:03:24,568 --> 01:03:26,170
in that car that day,
wasn't she?

1153
01:03:28,138 --> 01:03:29,273
Yes.

1154
01:03:31,876 --> 01:03:32,977
[INHALES SHARPLY]

1155
01:03:33,277 --> 01:03:35,612
That's just about enough
to break your heart.

1156
01:03:39,083 --> 01:03:40,117
Yes, it is.

1157
01:03:46,090 --> 01:03:47,191
Good night.

1158
01:03:58,002 --> 01:04:01,939
[CHURCH BELL TOLLING]

1159
01:04:12,616 --> 01:04:13,617
GEORGIA: Hmm.

1160
01:04:14,919 --> 01:04:17,121
-Banana pancakes.
-They're my favorite.

1161
01:04:17,387 --> 01:04:19,356
-Very impressive.
-Where are you off to?

1162
01:04:20,124 --> 01:04:22,359
Well, it is Sunday, and we

1163
01:04:22,492 --> 01:04:24,694
are good Christian women,
we're going to church.

1164
01:04:24,828 --> 01:04:25,963
I was gonna go
to my own church,

1165
01:04:26,096 --> 01:04:27,998
and I was hoping to bring
Jacey with me.

1166
01:04:28,598 --> 01:04:30,935
Well, maybe she could go
with me just this once.

1167
01:04:31,001 --> 01:04:33,537
Well, Jacey and I, we
were invited to this barbecue.

1168
01:04:33,670 --> 01:04:35,505
Some friends I haven't seen
in years.

1169
01:04:35,839 --> 01:04:38,308
Perhaps, you could pick her up
after the services.

1170
01:04:38,808 --> 01:04:40,077
Well, maybe you could
drop her off.

1171
01:04:41,411 --> 01:04:42,812
-Fine.
-All right.

1172
01:04:47,484 --> 01:04:51,621
-Uh-huh.
-CHOIR: * Early in the morning *

1173
01:04:51,755 --> 01:04:57,061
* Our song shall rise to Thee *

1174
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:00,164
Thank you.

1175
01:05:02,599 --> 01:05:06,971
* Merciful and mighty *

1176
01:05:07,237 --> 01:05:11,608
-* God in three persons *
-GEORGIA: Excuse us.

1177
01:05:12,276 --> 01:05:14,611
-Just slide in there, honey.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1178
01:05:16,513 --> 01:05:18,715
Why is everybody looking at us?

1179
01:05:18,848 --> 01:05:20,250
GEORGIA: They're looking
at our new dresses.

1180
01:05:20,384 --> 01:05:22,987
-PRIEST: Let us pray.
-You look like an angel morning.

1181
01:05:23,120 --> 01:05:26,390
Lord, we ask that you
guide us and defend us

1182
01:05:26,523 --> 01:05:28,292
in these turbulent times.

1183
01:05:29,026 --> 01:05:32,062
The world is not a simple place
and we are not perfect.

1184
01:05:33,063 --> 01:05:36,233
-Help us, Father, to be tolerant
of our brothers and sisters
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1185
01:05:36,366 --> 01:05:41,705
who were, like all of us,
created in your divine image.

1186
01:05:42,672 --> 01:05:44,341
-Amen.
-ALL: Amen.

1187
01:05:45,109 --> 01:05:50,147
* A mighty fortress is our God *

1188
01:05:50,280 --> 01:05:56,086
* A bulwark never failing *

1189
01:05:58,022 --> 01:05:59,689
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1190
01:06:00,024 --> 01:06:02,526
-[SHUSHES]
-Quiet.

1191
01:06:03,827 --> 01:06:05,695
Why do we have to be quiet?

1192
01:06:06,296 --> 01:06:08,732
That's just the way
they do things in this church.

1193
01:06:09,599 --> 01:06:11,735
Maybe you'll get in trouble
if you make noise.

1194
01:06:12,236 --> 01:06:14,171
JACEY: Not in my church.

1195
01:06:14,738 --> 01:06:16,673
I should have gone with Grandpa.

1196
01:06:18,475 --> 01:06:21,911
CHOIR: * His craft and power
Are great... *

1197
01:06:22,046 --> 01:06:24,248
[*****]

1198
01:06:24,381 --> 01:06:25,915
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1199
01:06:30,920 --> 01:06:32,889
-Grandpa.
-Hey, little bear.

1200
01:06:34,591 --> 01:06:36,093
-Thanks for bringing her.
-Oh, you're welcome.

1201
01:06:37,827 --> 01:06:40,364
Well, I'll-- I'll see you
in a little while then, honey.

1202
01:06:40,930 --> 01:06:42,432
Stay with us, Grandma.

1203
01:06:42,566 --> 01:06:44,934
-I don't think your grandma--
-Well, I'd love to stay.

1204
01:06:47,171 --> 01:06:48,205
Suit yourself.

1205
01:06:49,573 --> 01:06:51,508
-Come on, baby.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1206
01:06:54,811 --> 01:06:56,680
If you boys don't stop
chasing each other,

1207
01:06:56,813 --> 01:06:58,715
I'm going to separate you
for an hour.

1208
01:06:58,848 --> 01:07:00,717
-Do you hear me?
-[KIDS LAUGHING]

1209
01:07:00,850 --> 01:07:02,386
Go-- Would you go
get those boys?

1210
01:07:02,519 --> 01:07:04,454
-Mm-hmm.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1211
01:07:04,588 --> 01:07:06,456
-Hello.
-Hello.

1212
01:07:06,590 --> 01:07:08,092
GEORGIA: Oh,
this looks delicious.

1213
01:07:08,158 --> 01:07:10,660
Well, it's an old family
recipe from way back.

1214
01:07:10,794 --> 01:07:11,795
GEORGIA: Really?

1215
01:07:12,096 --> 01:07:13,863
-Would you like some?
-Oh, yeah, sure.

1216
01:07:14,131 --> 01:07:15,132
Just one.

1217
01:07:15,532 --> 01:07:16,766
-There you go.
-Thank you.

1218
01:07:17,334 --> 01:07:18,768
-Enjoy.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1219
01:07:20,504 --> 01:07:21,571
[LAUGHS]

1220
01:07:25,475 --> 01:07:28,778
-I wish I could dance like that.
-LOU: I'm sure you can.

1221
01:07:29,913 --> 01:07:30,914
You know...

1222
01:07:32,116 --> 01:07:34,584
we come from a family
of very, very talented people.

1223
01:07:35,152 --> 01:07:36,620
As a matter of fact
when I was young,

1224
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:38,788
I could dance as good as that.
Do you want to see?

1225
01:07:39,156 --> 01:07:41,024
-What about your foot?
-Don't worry about the foot.

1226
01:07:41,158 --> 01:07:42,592
Let's go. Come on.

1227
01:07:44,928 --> 01:07:49,899
[*****]

1228
01:07:54,003 --> 01:07:55,172
[WOMAN CHEERING]

1229
01:07:57,974 --> 01:08:00,277
-Yes.
-[WOMAN LAUGHS]

1230
01:08:01,145 --> 01:08:02,379
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1231
01:08:17,227 --> 01:08:19,263
-Yes.
-[LAUGHS]

1232
01:08:20,330 --> 01:08:21,598
What is she doing here?

1233
01:08:22,031 --> 01:08:23,300
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1234
01:08:32,409 --> 01:08:34,244
-GEORGIA: May I join you?
-Yes, you may.

1235
01:08:39,249 --> 01:08:40,384
[CHUCKLES]

1236
01:08:41,451 --> 01:08:42,852
JACEY: Grandma, did you see me?

1237
01:08:42,986 --> 01:08:45,389
Oh, yes, you look wonderful
out there.

1238
01:08:45,622 --> 01:08:47,757
I just used to love to dance
when I was your age.

1239
01:08:47,891 --> 01:08:48,992
Then come on.

1240
01:08:49,193 --> 01:08:50,227
GEORGIA: Oh, I don't know
that one, honey.

1241
01:08:50,360 --> 01:08:51,495
I'll teach you.

1242
01:08:53,697 --> 01:08:54,698
Okay.

1243
01:08:57,901 --> 01:09:01,938
One, two, three.
One, two, three.

1244
01:09:02,206 --> 01:09:06,743
One, two, three.
One, two, three.

1245
01:09:07,010 --> 01:09:09,213
-Then step back.
-[LAUGHS]

1246
01:09:12,349 --> 01:09:14,818
-Then you turn.
-[BOTH LAUGH]

1247
01:09:19,323 --> 01:09:20,790
Hey, I'm getting better.

1248
01:09:21,391 --> 01:09:22,592
[JACEY LAUGHING]

1249
01:09:25,229 --> 01:09:26,263
[GROANS]

1250
01:09:35,939 --> 01:09:37,073
[LOU GROANING]

1251
01:09:47,417 --> 01:09:48,618
[LOU GROANING]

1252
01:09:54,691 --> 01:09:56,260
[DOOR OPENING]

1253
01:09:57,461 --> 01:09:58,495
GEORGIA: My God.

1254
01:09:59,095 --> 01:10:00,764
-What happened?
-[BREATHES HEAVILY]

1255
01:10:02,131 --> 01:10:04,568
I'm fine. Go-- go on back
to bed.

1256
01:10:04,701 --> 01:10:06,770
-No. Come on. Come on.
-I'm fine.

1257
01:10:06,903 --> 01:10:08,338
-Just get on up there.
-[CLICKS TONGUE]

1258
01:10:08,738 --> 01:10:09,873
[GRUNTS]

1259
01:10:12,075 --> 01:10:13,209
-[GRUNTS]
-Okay.

1260
01:10:13,343 --> 01:10:15,245
-Slide back there.
-You-- you know, you go--

1261
01:10:15,379 --> 01:10:16,513
Put your--

1262
01:10:16,646 --> 01:10:19,983
Oh, my sweet Jesus.

1263
01:10:20,350 --> 01:10:23,353
-Oh, it's nothing. It's nothing.
-That is not nothing?

1264
01:10:23,487 --> 01:10:24,754
That is horrible.

1265
01:10:25,489 --> 01:10:27,524
Have you been doing everything
the doctor said?

1266
01:10:29,393 --> 01:10:30,494
LOU: Oh, it's--

1267
01:10:31,127 --> 01:10:32,396
it's hard for me to change
the bandage

1268
01:10:32,529 --> 01:10:35,365
-as often as I need to.
Oh, I didn't realize that.

1269
01:10:36,366 --> 01:10:38,868
I'm sorry. Oh.

1270
01:10:45,409 --> 01:10:46,843
Look, I-- I can take it
from here.

1271
01:10:46,976 --> 01:10:48,077
GEORGIA: Oh, I've got it.

1272
01:10:49,413 --> 01:10:50,480
-There.
-[GROANS]

1273
01:10:50,614 --> 01:10:52,282
-Am I hurting you?
-LOU: No, no, no.

1274
01:10:52,649 --> 01:10:54,217
-All right.
-[EXHALES]

1275
01:10:58,087 --> 01:10:59,088
[CHUCKLES]

1276
01:10:59,789 --> 01:11:01,157
Well, at least
you won't have to lock

1277
01:11:01,291 --> 01:11:02,659
your bedroom door anymore.

1278
01:11:03,793 --> 01:11:05,128
Clearly it's hard
for a Black man

1279
01:11:05,329 --> 01:11:06,796
to climb those steps
without his foot.

1280
01:11:07,096 --> 01:11:09,566
I am an old-fashioned,

1281
01:11:09,699 --> 01:11:11,635
-moral, southern woman.
-LOU: Uh-huh.

1282
01:11:11,768 --> 01:11:14,070
I wouldn't care if you were pink
with purple polka dots.

1283
01:11:14,203 --> 01:11:15,539
-[LAUGHS]
-You're still a man,

1284
01:11:15,672 --> 01:11:17,841
and I still would lock my door.

1285
01:11:18,375 --> 01:11:20,844
-I see.
-No, you don't.

1286
01:11:22,579 --> 01:11:23,547
All right.

1287
01:11:24,180 --> 01:11:25,382
Let's get back in bed.

1288
01:11:25,882 --> 01:11:28,352
Come on, now. Come on.

1289
01:11:31,187 --> 01:11:32,221
[LOU EXHALES DEEPLY]

1290
01:11:32,989 --> 01:11:36,360
You know I'm-- I'm sorry
about this afternoon.

1291
01:11:37,761 --> 01:11:40,430
I'm sure it was uncomfortable
being with my people.

1292
01:11:40,564 --> 01:11:42,198
No, not at all.

1293
01:11:43,132 --> 01:11:45,234
I was just happy
to crash the party.

1294
01:11:45,369 --> 01:11:47,203
Yeah, right. [GRUNTS]

1295
01:11:48,004 --> 01:11:49,773
I'm sure you would have
felt much more at home

1296
01:11:49,906 --> 01:11:51,941
with your Georgia Peaches
at the fancy dinner.

1297
01:11:54,043 --> 01:11:56,480
-When is that dinner?
-That was tonight.

1298
01:11:58,382 --> 01:11:59,516
Oh, I'm sorry.

1299
01:12:01,250 --> 01:12:03,420
For what?

1300
01:12:03,553 --> 01:12:06,990
It seems impossible for Lily
to have been raised

1301
01:12:07,123 --> 01:12:09,893
by you and your husband
and still come out so special.

1302
01:12:10,126 --> 01:12:11,428
-Really?
-[GRUNTS]

1303
01:12:12,996 --> 01:12:14,398
I take that thought back.

1304
01:12:17,767 --> 01:12:19,536
-[CLICKS TONGUE] Good night.
-Good night.

1305
01:12:23,707 --> 01:12:24,974
-[*****]
-[LAUGHS]

1306
01:12:27,176 --> 01:12:28,978
[SIGHS] It's hot.

1307
01:12:29,513 --> 01:12:31,280
-GEORGIA: That's true.
-[WOMAN SIGHING]

1308
01:12:32,549 --> 01:12:35,218
This park has gone
to hell in a hand basket.

1309
01:12:35,652 --> 01:12:38,287
Time was you could come here
and have pleasant afternoon.

1310
01:12:39,155 --> 01:12:40,189
[CHUCKLES]

1311
01:12:40,490 --> 01:12:43,059
The handsome devil
over there is my grandson.

1312
01:12:43,893 --> 01:12:47,697
The boy's got two speeds,
red hot fire and coma.

1313
01:12:47,831 --> 01:12:49,065
I can hardly keep up with him.

1314
01:12:50,066 --> 01:12:51,901
That's my granddaughter
over there.

1315
01:12:53,002 --> 01:12:55,171
-Where?
-GEORGIA: On the swing.

1316
01:12:56,105 --> 01:12:58,307
That's Jacey. That's my baby.

1317
01:12:58,708 --> 01:13:01,945
I see. Well, isn't she adorable?

1318
01:13:02,612 --> 01:13:03,647
I think so.

1319
01:13:04,914 --> 01:13:07,250
I'm going to start
wrapping things up, okay?

1320
01:13:07,451 --> 01:13:08,485
-GEORGIA: Sure.
-LOU: Yeah.

1321
01:13:08,818 --> 01:13:11,455
-So, is this your husband?
-LOU: Oh, no, ma'am.

1322
01:13:12,456 --> 01:13:13,623
We just live together.

1323
01:13:14,458 --> 01:13:15,659
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1324
01:13:17,026 --> 01:13:18,361
[WOMAN CHUCKLING]

1325
01:13:21,665 --> 01:13:23,066
Well, really.

1326
01:13:25,334 --> 01:13:26,536
[CHUCKLES]

1327
01:13:27,203 --> 01:13:29,673
I do believe
that global warming

1328
01:13:29,806 --> 01:13:31,374
is concentrating on Georgia.

1329
01:13:31,508 --> 01:13:33,677
-[LOU SCOFFING] Impossible.
-Grandma told me

1330
01:13:33,810 --> 01:13:35,679
they have more sun here
in the south.

1331
01:13:35,812 --> 01:13:37,013
Oh, it's true.

1332
01:13:39,382 --> 01:13:42,285
You, uh, say it's a little
too hot here in Georgia?

1333
01:13:42,486 --> 01:13:43,620
Yeah.

1334
01:13:46,189 --> 01:13:49,493
Maybe you need
a nice cold shower.

1335
01:13:49,726 --> 01:13:51,027
Yes, ma'am,
that would be perfect.

1336
01:13:51,294 --> 01:13:52,295
[MOUTHS] One...

1337
01:13:53,229 --> 01:13:54,230
two...

1338
01:13:55,932 --> 01:13:57,701
-three!
-[BOTH LAUGH]

1339
01:13:57,934 --> 01:13:59,368
Oh. Oh, you.

1340
01:13:59,503 --> 01:14:01,270
-All right, all right.
-LOU: Let's go get her.

1341
01:14:01,404 --> 01:14:03,006
-[BOTH LAUGH]
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1342
01:14:03,139 --> 01:14:05,208
-[*****]
-This is it, this is it. Okay.

1343
01:14:08,244 --> 01:14:10,313
All right. This is it.

1344
01:14:11,214 --> 01:14:12,949
Okay. There you go.

1345
01:14:13,950 --> 01:14:16,620
LOU: Oh, yeah? I'mma get you.
Watch this, watch this.

1346
01:14:17,554 --> 01:14:19,989
[GRUNTS, LAUGHS]

1347
01:14:25,394 --> 01:14:26,563
[ALL LAUGH]

1348
01:14:42,879 --> 01:14:44,147
It's getting late.

1349
01:14:44,748 --> 01:14:46,115
We should be thinking
about dinner.

1350
01:14:51,621 --> 01:14:54,624
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1351
01:14:55,825 --> 01:14:58,361
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

1352
01:15:00,664 --> 01:15:03,232
-[SIREN WAILING]
-[*****]

1353
01:15:08,572 --> 01:15:09,573
[JACEY TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

1354
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:12,308
Are you all right, honey?

1355
01:15:12,909 --> 01:15:14,911
-No, no.
-LOU: Little bear.

1356
01:15:15,579 --> 01:15:19,415
No. No. No. No.

1357
01:15:19,816 --> 01:15:20,950
No.

1358
01:15:25,354 --> 01:15:28,291
[CRYING] Come back.

1359
01:15:28,992 --> 01:15:31,027
Please come back.

1360
01:15:31,828 --> 01:15:33,830
-Mom.
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1361
01:15:37,133 --> 01:15:41,070
JACEY: Come back!
Mommy, come back!

1362
01:15:41,204 --> 01:15:43,206
Mommy, don't leave me!

1363
01:15:46,843 --> 01:15:49,012
-LOU: Little bear, it's okay.
-Mommy! Let me go!

1364
01:15:49,145 --> 01:15:50,614
-LOU: No, no, it's okay.
-Let me go!

1365
01:15:50,714 --> 01:15:51,815
I know, I know.

1366
01:15:51,948 --> 01:15:54,951
-I want Mommy and Daddy!
-LOU: I know, I know.

1367
01:15:55,084 --> 01:15:57,320
JACEY: Let me go! [CRYING]

1368
01:15:59,789 --> 01:16:01,224
GEORGIA: It's all right,
it's okay.

1369
01:16:01,357 --> 01:16:04,227
Your Grandpa and I, uh,
we'll always be here

1370
01:16:04,360 --> 01:16:05,695
forever and ever.

1371
01:16:06,395 --> 01:16:08,231
-It'll be all right.
-[JACEY CRYING]

1372
01:16:17,707 --> 01:16:24,513
[*****]

1373
01:16:27,684 --> 01:16:28,818
Is she asleep?

1374
01:16:30,920 --> 01:16:33,957
She's starting to remember
everything about the accident.

1375
01:16:35,558 --> 01:16:38,127
I can't even imagine
what she must be feeling.

1376
01:16:39,295 --> 01:16:41,097
Well, school starts
in a couple of weeks.

1377
01:16:42,065 --> 01:16:43,867
Maybe, uh, when she's around
her-- her teachers

1378
01:16:44,000 --> 01:16:46,002
and her friends
and everything's on schedule...

1379
01:16:47,704 --> 01:16:49,005
everything might go back
to normal.

1380
01:16:49,472 --> 01:16:50,674
[SIGHS]

1381
01:16:51,775 --> 01:16:53,042
Our children are gone.

1382
01:16:54,477 --> 01:16:58,815
And that little child upstairs
is suffering God knows what.

1383
01:17:01,150 --> 01:17:03,052
Every bit of it is my fault.

1384
01:17:04,253 --> 01:17:06,122
-What?
-I was weak.

1385
01:17:06,823 --> 01:17:10,359
I was so weak. I was--
I don't understand it.

1386
01:17:11,294 --> 01:17:12,361
I should have just--

1387
01:17:12,996 --> 01:17:14,197
I should have done
what you said.

1388
01:17:14,330 --> 01:17:15,398
I should have stopped him.

1389
01:17:15,531 --> 01:17:17,333
I shouldn't have let him
go out there that night.

1390
01:17:17,701 --> 01:17:18,968
And I should have stayed
with Lily

1391
01:17:19,102 --> 01:17:20,336
when she asked me,
and I didn't.

1392
01:17:20,704 --> 01:17:22,839
-And I don't know why.
-You left with him
because you knew

1393
01:17:22,972 --> 01:17:24,908
that if he was home
beating on you,

1394
01:17:25,742 --> 01:17:27,143
he wouldn't be able
to hurt them.

1395
01:17:27,977 --> 01:17:29,345
It's not your fault.

1396
01:17:29,478 --> 01:17:32,448
I should have taken her away
years ago when she was a baby.

1397
01:17:32,581 --> 01:17:34,517
I should have just gotten
her out of the house.

1398
01:17:35,018 --> 01:17:36,552
What was I so scared of?

1399
01:17:37,721 --> 01:17:40,389
[SNIFFLES] I just want
another chance.

1400
01:17:40,523 --> 01:17:42,458
I just want to go back. I...

1401
01:17:43,392 --> 01:17:44,593
I want to fight for her.

1402
01:17:45,028 --> 01:17:46,730
-That's what you're doing.
-[CRYING]

1403
01:17:48,865 --> 01:17:49,966
That's what you're doing now...

1404
01:17:51,467 --> 01:17:53,870
you're fighting for that child.
[SHUSHING]

1405
01:18:00,176 --> 01:18:01,745
Everything's going to be
just fine.

1406
01:18:04,113 --> 01:18:05,782
-Hey.
-[SNIFFLES]

1407
01:18:06,115 --> 01:18:07,116
Hey.

1408
01:18:11,354 --> 01:18:12,956
He can't hurt you anymore.

1409
01:18:15,825 --> 01:18:16,993
-[GEORGIA CHUCKLING]
-Hmm.

1410
01:18:32,776 --> 01:18:33,977
I must go to Jacey.

1411
01:18:35,211 --> 01:18:38,948
[*****]

1412
01:19:12,615 --> 01:19:13,950
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1413
01:19:16,685 --> 01:19:18,254
-LOU: Did you take a bite?
-[JACEY TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

1414
01:19:18,387 --> 01:19:21,891
LOU: We're toasting marshmallows
out here in the sand.

1415
01:19:23,392 --> 01:19:24,994
Oh, this gonna be-- Quick,
quick, quick, quick, quick.

1416
01:19:25,128 --> 01:19:26,629
-It's on fire.
-Oh, it's on fire.

1417
01:19:26,830 --> 01:19:27,997
Blow, blow, blow.

1418
01:19:29,198 --> 01:19:31,534
Oh, okay.
This one's better than this one.

1419
01:19:31,835 --> 01:19:32,902
Blow it out.

1420
01:19:33,702 --> 01:19:34,838
Okay, now try it.

1421
01:19:36,072 --> 01:19:37,140
-How's it taste?
-Yummy.

1422
01:19:37,273 --> 01:19:38,474
Ooh, that's good, huh?

1423
01:19:38,607 --> 01:19:39,642
-Let me see.
-Mm-hmm.

1424
01:19:39,843 --> 01:19:41,244
[GROANS]

1425
01:19:43,446 --> 01:19:45,648
This is the third marshmallow,
do you think you stand it?

1426
01:19:47,650 --> 01:19:50,719
We're toasting marshmallows
out here in sand.

1427
01:19:50,854 --> 01:19:52,321
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

1428
01:19:56,459 --> 01:19:57,526
What are you doing?

1429
01:20:01,697 --> 01:20:03,666
I've imposed
on your hospitality too long.

1430
01:20:04,868 --> 01:20:06,369
You're taking her, aren't you?

1431
01:20:13,509 --> 01:20:14,610
I...

1432
01:20:16,479 --> 01:20:17,613
I need to tell you something.

1433
01:20:20,616 --> 01:20:21,717
Marcus and Lily...

1434
01:20:24,320 --> 01:20:25,554
they was going to move
back here.

1435
01:20:27,790 --> 01:20:28,892
What are you saying?

1436
01:20:29,926 --> 01:20:31,127
They wanted to come home.

1437
01:20:32,061 --> 01:20:33,762
They wanted to live
in my old house.

1438
01:20:33,963 --> 01:20:34,931
Why didn't you tell me?

1439
01:20:35,198 --> 01:20:36,665
Because I didn't want them
to move here.

1440
01:20:36,799 --> 01:20:40,103
I was against Jacey
being raised here.

1441
01:20:41,037 --> 01:20:43,539
And I thought
that if you knew,

1442
01:20:43,873 --> 01:20:47,343
uh, you'd try and keep her.
And I couldn't let that happen.

1443
01:20:49,845 --> 01:20:52,081
Um, I just didn't trust you
to raise her.

1444
01:20:52,315 --> 01:20:56,219
-So, why are you telling me now?
-Because now, I know I'm wrong.

1445
01:20:57,820 --> 01:20:59,255
She belongs with you.

1446
01:21:00,823 --> 01:21:01,891
You're a good mother...

1447
01:21:04,227 --> 01:21:05,794
good woman.

1448
01:21:07,030 --> 01:21:08,164
She needs you.

1449
01:21:10,399 --> 01:21:11,400
[SNIFFLES]

1450
01:21:13,402 --> 01:21:14,637
She's lucky to have you.

1451
01:21:15,804 --> 01:21:17,073
GEORGIA: She needs you, too.

1452
01:21:17,440 --> 01:21:20,343
This is crazy.
What are you doing?

1453
01:21:24,313 --> 01:21:25,848
Is this because of last night?

1454
01:21:30,219 --> 01:21:31,554
I pulled away from you,

1455
01:21:33,122 --> 01:21:34,557
but it wasn't because
you're Black.

1456
01:21:36,692 --> 01:21:37,994
It's because you're a man.

1457
01:21:46,635 --> 01:21:47,636
[BAG ZIPS]

1458
01:21:48,471 --> 01:21:49,672
I think I better go.

1459
01:21:51,274 --> 01:21:54,843
[*****]

1460
01:22:22,138 --> 01:22:23,372
Morning, honey.

1461
01:22:24,040 --> 01:22:25,174
What's that?

1462
01:22:25,908 --> 01:22:28,377
-Grandpa went away for a while.
-I know.

1463
01:22:28,511 --> 01:22:30,413
He told me to give you this.

1464
01:22:31,180 --> 01:22:32,148
Oh?

1465
01:22:32,815 --> 01:22:34,217
See, now what we have to do,

1466
01:22:34,350 --> 01:22:35,618
we have to get you
over to that school

1467
01:22:35,751 --> 01:22:37,053
and get you registered,

1468
01:22:37,186 --> 01:22:39,255
because first grade is going
